title: lemon pie(lemonade)
directions: Mix lemonade and milk together.
Add sugar, Cool Whip and coloring.
Mix well.
Pour into baked pie crusts.
Chill and serve.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Chill, then peel and grate.
Combine cheese, milk and butter in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until butter and cheese melt. Remove from heat and stir in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper. Fold cheese mixture into potatoes.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mama's pineapple coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce oven temperature to 325° and bake until done. This recipe will make 1 large pie or 2 small ones.

title: noodles romanoff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place cooked noodles in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over noodles. Mix.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple into small pan, being careful to drain well.
To the syrup, add sugar and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice and cheese spread.
Stir.
Add dissolved gelatin and chill until partially set.
Stir in pineapple, nuts and oranges. Fold in Cool Whip and pour into 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: currant pie
directions: Mix all well and cook over medium heat until thick.
Add to baked 8-inch
pie shell.
Top with beaten 2 egg whites, 4 tablespoons sugar, pinch of salt and 1/2 tablespoon vanilla.

title: broccoli and turkey
directions: Heat butter,
flour,
milk
and cheese over medium heat until cheese melts.
Cook broccoli a few minutes with salt and pepper to taste.
In baking dish, layer turkey, then broccoli. Pour sauce over.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apples in
medium
size	glass baking dish.
Mix together flour, sugar
and	cinnamon in a bowl.
Cut in margarine until mixture
is crumbly.	Sprinkle over apples.
Sprinkle water on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rum balls
directions: In a saucepan melt chocolate chips over low heat.
Stir in sugar, rum and corn syrup.
Fold in vanilla wafers and nuts. Shape into 1 inch balls (2 tsp. mix for each).
Roll in sugar. Store in airtight container for several days.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: crowning glory
directions: Combine 1/2 can soup with remaining ingredients, except bacon. Mix thoroughly.
In shallow baking pan, shape firmly into ring (2 inches high with 4 inch opening).
Place bacon on ring.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spoon off fat.
Top loaf with remaining soup. Bake 5 to 7 minutes more.
Serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chili cheese snacks
directions: In small bowl, beat cream cheese, chilies, olives, onions, Cheddar cheese and hot pepper sauce.
Separate each tube of crescent dough into four rectangles, pressing perforations to seal.
Spread and press cheese mixture over dough.
Roll up jellyroll style.
Cut each roll into 10 slices and place on greased baking sheets.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Yield: 80 appetizers.

title: beef and cabbage stew
directions: Brown meat with onions.
Pour into heavy kettle with all ingredients.
Cook on slow heat until done.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Combine cake mix, Cool Whip and egg.
Drop
by teaspoon into powdered sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy pan, over low heat, melt chips with milk, vanilla and salt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts.
Cool 10 to 12 minutes on aluminum foil.
Form into football shape.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.

title: creamed peas and new potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; remove a narrow strip of peel around the center of each.
Cook potatoes until tender; drain.
Meanwhile, cook peas and drain.
Cook onions in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook about 2 minutes longer.
Stir in vegetables.

title: zippy blue cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into a ball shape and roll in ground walnuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: basic pie filling
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add enough milk to make a paste; mix well.
Add remaining milk, hot water and beaten egg yolks.
Add butter, vanilla and marshmallows.
Cook over medium heat, stirring at all times, until marshmallows melt and mixture is thick.
Pour in baked crust; top with meringue.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle 2/3 crumbs in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine egg whites, granulated sugar, berries and lemon juice.
Beat at high speed about 10 minutes.
Whip cream; fold in. Spoon over crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze 6 hours. Serves 12.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain.
Add 1/2 cup oleo.
Mash.
Mix sugar, egg, mayo, onion and salt.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with 2 tablespoons oleo.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together, then add broccoli.
Place into greased 10 x 10-inch pan and bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into small squares and serve.

title: fruit compote
directions: Mix fruit together gently in a large salad bowl.
Pour orange juice over fruit and toss gently to coat thoroughly.
Chill and serve.

title: broiled tomatoes with parmesan butter
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Sprinkle tomatoes with seasonings and broil 10 minutes.
Spread with butter mixture and broil 5 more minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Save broth.
Grease casserole dish (use oil).
Tear chicken into small bites.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soups and 1 cup broth together.
Pour over chicken.
Mix butter, 1 cup broth and Stove Top dressing mixture over soups in casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 325° to 350°.
Beat eggs; add sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients to mixture.
Add nuts and carrots.
Bake 1 hour in slow oven in lightly greased and floured pan.

title: scottish oatcakes(kids' stuff and special effects food)
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Mix in rolled oats.
Cut in butter thoroughly.
Gradually add milk, stirring until dough forms.
Roll dough on lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Place on greased (sprayed) baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice separately according to package directions.
Cool and prepare dressing.
Refrigerate.
In large saute pan, melt butter and add vegetables.
Saute until tender.
Combine with rice.
Add Italian dressing to taste; toss and chill until ready to serve. Serve atop fresh greens.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes and pine nuts.
(Travels well, it's pretty and it's healthy.)

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil the chicken until done and remove meat from bones.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix the chicken, sour cream, cream of chicken soup and water chestnuts.
Place in casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and stir in butter and poppy seed.
Spoon cracker mixture over casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crab au gratin
directions: In medium size pan, melt butter and add flour.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly to keep smooth and free from lumps. Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.

title: blumenkohlcremesuppe(cream of cauliflower soup)
directions: Place the water and bouillon cube in a saucepan and heat until the bouillon cube dissolves.
Break the cauliflower into flowerets and cook in the bouillon until tender.
Remove the cauliflower and select about 8 flowerets which are most intact and set aside.
Chop or puree the remainder.
Melt the butter in a saucepan and add the flour, stirring constantly.
Cook for 1 to 2 minutes, then add the cauliflower puree and the cooking liquid.
Stirring constantly, add the milk or cream, salt and nutmeg.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Add the cheese and the reserved flowerets.
Serve in individual dishes. Sprinkle with chives, parsley, dill and croutons before serving.

title: chili
directions: In a large boiler, bring beans and tomato paste to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer.
In a skillet, brown hamburger meat.
Add Chili-O mix and stir well.
Pour into bean mixture and let simmer until ready to eat.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: summer berry pie
directions: Mix berries in large bowl.
Pour in pie shell.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water until smooth. Stirring constantly, cook on medium heat until mixture comes to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour over berries in pie shell.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Spread Cool Whip over pie before serving.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage.
Keep half of the drippings in skillet.
Add flour, salt and pepper, stirring until browned lightly.
Add milk; stir until thickened.
Turn heat off.
Add cooked sausage.

title: sticky bread
directions: You will need a large Bundt pan.

title: flank steak on the grill
directions: Combine all ingredients (except flank steak). Mix.
Makes about 3 1/4 cups of marinade.
Put flank steak in marinade and refrigerate several hours or overnight. Grill.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add margarine and vinegar; stir well.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: pear cake
directions: Stir and let stand 1 hour.
Stir 3 or 4 times during hour in one large mixing bowl.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: raisin broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli flowerets and stems; add next 3 ingredients.

title: "mama's" chicken casserole
directions: Boil, debone chicken and break into small pieces. Dice onion. Shred cheese. Mix together soups and Ro-Tel, then bring to a boil. Layer all in pan and cook in oven for 30 minutes at 350°. Pour 1/2 can chicken broth over Doritos if needed.

title: pork chops, bavarian style
directions: Cover bottom of dish with bacon.
Top bacon with sauerkraut, about 1-inch layer.
Lay chops close together on top of sauerkraut and top the chops with a layer of onion.
Next, a layer of potatoes.
Cover with mashed tomatoes.
Season with pepper and sprinkle of caraway seed.
Cover and bake about 2 hours at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Line pie plate with 9-inch pie crust.
Combine in a blender or mixing bowl all the ingredients except the egg whites.
Mix well. Fold beaten egg whites into pie filling.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 375° and continue to bake for 30 minutes or until filling is set.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients, except black beans and vinegar, in saucepan; saute.
Add black beans; simmer 20 minutes.
Add vinegar, stir and serve over rice.

title: unbaked fruitcake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Press in loaf pans.
Let set until firm.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Combine water, vinegar, sugar and salt and bring to a boil; set aside.
Cover sliced cabbage with fresh water and bring to a boil.
Drain and return cabbage to pot.
Add sweet and sour mixture to cabbage.
Melt lard in small frypan.
Add tip of small onion. Remove onion as soon as it browns.
While stirring lard, add flour.
Stir and keep smooth (don't brown).
Add lard mixture to cabbage.
Stir and simmer 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna and cheese casserole
directions: Drain tuna. Mix together with soup. Mix pasta, broccoli and milk. Add salt and pepper to taste. Add in Parmesan cheese. Mix well. Bake in a 9 x 13 baking dish at 350°.
Cover with other 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, Cheddar cheese and breadcrumbs.
Bake until golden brown. May add granulated garlic if desired. Serves 8.

title: 6 pound fudge
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, butter and condensed milk.
In Yuma, boil exactly 8 minutes.
Stir all the time.
Remove from heat.
Mix marshmallows, marshmallow dip, chocolate bars, chocolate chips and nut meats and pour hot mixture over in large container and store just enough to mix well.
Pour in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chris' chocolate intrigue cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients. Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour 2/3 of batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and cream of tartar.
Add flour mixture gradually to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Wrap in wax paper rolls.
Chill.
Cut.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time. Add milk and flour alternately. Cook in 4 (9-inch) layer pans for 20 to 30 minutes, until done.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer pineapple, pie filling and cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Slice margarine into thin slices and lay over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Stir in cheese while hot.
Put crushed crackers in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Add cooked broccoli mixture.
Put another layer of crackers on top.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes on High, 8 to 12 minutes.
Peel and slice. Melt butter; whisk in flour and add milk gradually.
Microwave on High 6 minutes.
Stir every 2 minutes until sauce thickens.
Add cheese, chilies and garlic powder.
Mix sauce with potatoes.
Top with bread crumbs.
Cover and microwave on High 7 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and butter. Cover and let stand 20 minutes. Then add the remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: best ever apple butter by katie freeman
directions: Place applesauce in a large saucepan.
On medium heat, bring to a slow boil.
Add sugar and spices.
When dissolved, bring mixture back to a boil.
Add margarine; cook until melted and blended.
Put in jars and seal.
Yields 4 pints.

title: cinnamon candy roll
directions: Cook to soft ball stage.
Beat; when creamy, pour onto wax paper that is covered with cinnamon, then roll.
Cool and slice.

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Mix sugar, flour and cocoa and add to butter.
Combine egg yolks and milk and add to mixture.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.

title: good chili
directions: Place meat in large pan.
Cook until meat turns white.
It makes its own broth.
Mix all seasonings together and add meat. Cook 2 hours or so.

title: special hawaiian punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes and add remaining ingredients, except 7-Up.
Mix well and freeze.
Thaw 2 hours before using.
Add 2-quarts 7-Up.

title: apple dessert
directions: Butter a dish.
Sprinkle jello over apples.
Mix flour, sugar and margarine; crumble over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan, saute celery and onion in butter until tender.
Add potatoes and broth.
Simmer until potatoes are done. Stir in milk and seasonings; heat through.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Serves 8.

title: better than s-- cake
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, bake cake according to package directions. Meanwhile, in medium saucepan, combine pineapple with its juice and sugar; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thick and syrupy, about 20 minutes.
When cake is done, remove from oven and pierce top with a fork at 1-inch intervals.
Pour on pineapple mixture and spread evenly over cake.
Cool completely. In medium bowl, combine pudding mix with milk; blend until thick. Spread over cake.
In medium bowl, beat cream until stiff peaks form.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla; continue beating until stiff.
Spread over cake.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Before serving, sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Makes 16 servings.
Prep time:
20 minutes, plus standing.
Baking time:
35 minutes.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream shortening.
Add 1/2 of sugar, then 1/2 water as you blend.
Continue to add sugar, then water, until all is used.
Add salt and flavoring.
Will store in fridge for several weeks or in freezer for several months.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Cook and chop finely the chicken.
Mix in spices.
Add mayonnaise.
Wash and cut tops off tomatoes.
Hollow out centers of tomatoes.
Fill with chicken mix with a spoon or open tip of pastry bag.
Handle tomatoes gently to prevent squishing.
Serve as appetizers.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
Add beans with juice and taco mix.
Simmer a few minutes and cool.
Mix all ingredients together and add chips when serving.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, add pumpkin and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add vanilla.
Add walnuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: grandma's shortbread cookies
directions: Mix and chill dough.
Roll into small balls.
Press cookies with bottom of glass which has been dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.
Makes 160 to 170 cookies.

title: sweet potato pie(club member: brad smith)
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender. Place in mixing bowl.
Add oleo and sugar. Beat free of lumps. Add vanilla, milk and eggs. Place in unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 400° until firm.

title: easy pumpkin dip
directions: In a large bowl, combine pumpkin, dry pudding mix and spices. Fold in cool whip. Chill until ready to serve. Serve with apple slices, ginger snaps or vanilla wafers.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Add baking powder, baking soda and salt to sifted flour and sift together.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Mix well and set aside.

title: blueberry dream pie
directions: Slice one thin layer of banana on bottom of pie crusts.
Whip Dream Whip as directed on package.
Beat cream cheese, confectioners sugar and lemon juice until smooth.
Add to Dream Whip and mix until smooth.
Spoon onto top of bananas, then top with the blueberry pie filling.
Chill.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Chill dough overnight.
Take about 1 teaspoon of dough and roll into a ball.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Use a smooth bottomed glass (covered with margarine) and press down balls, dipping into sugar each time.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add 1 cup water.
Heat until boiling and pour over Jell-O and stir until dissolved. Add cream cheese and other ingredients in order.
Last, fold in whipped cream. Chill until firm.

title: chili colorado
directions: Soak chilies in hot water 35 to 40 minutes until softened. Drain.
Remove seeds and discard.
Grind chilies in amount of beef stock to make a paste. Dredge meat cubes in flour mixed with salt. Brown meat on all sides in hot oil.
Add garlic, oregano and cumin.
Pour remaining beef stock into chili paste and add to meat.
Cover until tender, about 2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: make ahead potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Beat sour cream and cream cheese together.
Add hot potatoes and beat until smooth.
Add butter, chives and salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: doc. icebox rolls
directions: Cream shortenin' and sugah; add salt and boilin' watah.
Beat egg and add.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm watah.
Add flour and mix good.
Cover and put in icebox.
Make out rolls 'bout 2 hours before bakin'.
Put on a greased pan and brush with melted buttah. Let rise in a warm place.
Bake in oven at 400° to 425° til pretty light brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve and jump outta the way.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Salt and soda are not necessary if using self-rising flour.

title: mexican pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease pie plate.
Stir egg and green onions into mashed potatoes and press into pie plate evenly across and up sides.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until light brown.
Cook beef and drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Spoon into potato shell and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes more.
Garnish with sour cream, tomato, avocado and lettuce.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Cook in boiling water to cover 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Combine potatoes and Italian salad dressing.
Chill.
Carefully stir celery and green onions into potato mixture.
Combine sour cream and next 2 ingredients; stir well.
Pour mixture over potatoes; toss gently. Garnish with green onion tops if desired.

title: alabama dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly. Drain. Combine cheese, tomatoes, picante sauce and soup in slow cooker. Cook on low until cheese melts. Mix well. Stir in meat mixture. Cook until heated through. Serve with nacho chips.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook diced squash and onions; drain and add pimentos, sour cream and soup.
Butter casserole and sprinkle half of stuffing in bottom.
Dot with melted butter.
Add squash mixture, then rest of stuffing and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas trash
directions: Mix ingredients for sauce.
Mix all dry ingredients well in big pan.
Drizzle sauce over dry ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 275°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
When cool, store in airtight containers.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Stir in sugar.
Add remaining ingredients, adding ginger ale and sherbet just before serving.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Stir all ingredients together.
Cover and chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in small amount of oil or butter.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Cook rice as directed on package. Drain broccoli.
Combine all ingredients except crackers and mix well.
Pour into 2-quart Pyrex dish.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Spread crushed crackers over top and bake 10 additional minutes.

title: turkey stroganoff
directions: Cook green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Blend soup, sour cream and salt.
Add onion, green pepper and cooked noodles and turkey.
Mix well.
Turn into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbles.
Serves 10 to 12.
This dish freezes well and keeps for a month.

title: homemade salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs.
Pour into pan with vinegar and melted margarine. Let cook until curdles.
Pour over lettuce mixture and mix well. Slice boiled eggs over salad.

title: symphony bars(yields 32 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour and salt.
Gradually add to cream mixture.
Blend in nuts.
Divide dough in half.
Add chocolate to one-half and spread white layer in bottom of pan, then spread chocolate layer on top. Bake 30 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add meat; cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Remove meat from marinade.
Alternate meat and vegetables on 4 skewers.
Place on grill and cook according to taste for steak.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together. Add 1 small can crushed pineapple and 2 cups flour. Mix well. Grease and flour cake pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: dried sweet corn
directions: Cook on top of stove on a low heat for 20 minutes or more. Stir often as this will stick and scorch very easily.
Put in dryer; stir often as it dries.
Store in freezer if kept for any length of time.

title: pumpkin pie crunch
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar, salt and spices.
Pour in pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pumpkin mixture.
Dribble melted oleo, then nuts, over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown the ground beef and pour the grease off.
Boil the water in a large pot for the spaghetti until cooked.
Pour off water. Put spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce in the pot of ground beef. Add the onion, bell pepper, celery and seasoning to your taste. Let simmer for 10 minutes.
It is ready to eat.
Serves 6.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken soup and rice; place in casserole.
Pour about 1/2 cup uncooked rice over top.
Pour the chicken soup over top.
Cover with water.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: frosted meat loaf
directions: In saucepan, mix soups, poultry seasoning and onion; blend well.
Cook until bubbly on medium heat.
Pat ground beef into oblong pan, like you use for sheet cake.
Cover meat with bread cubes.
Pour soup mixture over bread cubes.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: angel fluff
directions: Beat Jell-O and water until foamy.
Add strawberries; whip until foamy.
Crumble and add cake to Jell-O mixture a little at a time.
Fold in gently.
Put into mold.
When set, frost with whipped cream.

title: lela's tamale pie
directions: Brown beef; add next 3 ingredients and keep hot until the topping is made.
Mix cornbread mix according to directions.
Pour meat mixture in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour cornbread mixture over meat mixture and spread.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in 400° oven. Serve hot.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place the above ingredients into a 13 x 9 x 2 glass dish or metal pan cover with homemade crust.
Place in a 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pound chicken breasts to flatten. Place one slice of cheese over each chicken breast.
Place three asparagus spears or three broccoli flowerets in center of dish. Place two half slices of bacon on top.
Sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon bread crumbs.
Bring two sides of chicken together and secure with wooden pick.
Place seam side down in buttered 2-quart rectangular baking dish.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients after thoroughly draining fruit. Chill well for several hours and serve.
Cherries are an optional garnish or use pecans.

title: duck
directions: Salt and pepper duck.
Put in Dutch Oven on top of stove.
Add ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, onions, bay leaf, oregano and poultry seasoning.
Add water to cover.
Cook 3-1/2 hours.
Debone. Add water if necessary.
Cook 30 minutes longer.

title: beef birds
directions: Pound steak, cut into 3 x 4-inch pieces.
Combine ingredients, except mustard.
Spread mustard on steak pieces, then add filling. Roll up and fasten with toothpicks.
Brown in butter, then simmer with bouillon cubes and 2 cups water for 45 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: white wine coolers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir and add a few melon balls.

title: coconut crumb cherry pie
directions: Bake pie shell at 450° for 5 minutes.
Bring pie filling just to a boil in a saucepan; pour into warm pie shell.
Combine flour and sugar.
Stir in butter.
Add coconut and stir with fork until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until browned.
Cool.

title: pa's molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix first 4 ingredients well in large bowl. Sift dry ingredients, omitting the 1/4 cup sugar. Add dry ingredients to molasses mixture. Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Roll in 1/4 cup sugar. Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: parkerhouse gooey coffee cake
directions: Mix together well and sprinkle over the rolls.
Place a damp cloth over pan.
Let set overnight (or can place uncovered in a cold oven overnight).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out on plate or platter.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and crushed potato chips.
Place all other ingredients in a large rectangular 12 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Top with cheese and potato chips.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. (Can serve cold.)

title: potato fluff candy
directions: Gradually work sugar into potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients. Press into greased pan and let stand in a cool place for 24 hours. Cut into squares.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until soft.
Peel and slice and place in slow cooker.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over sweet potatoes.
Cover and cook on high for 4 hours.

title: creamy potato casserole
directions: 1. Cook potatoes until tender.
Mash potatoes using hand mixer, add salt, cream cheese and chives, butter, garlic salt and pepper, mix until smooth.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Skin and bone chicken breasts; cut chicken into 1-inch squares.
Saute onion and pepper in 2 tablespoons of hot oil in a large skillet, stirring until vegetables are crisp and tender. Remove to dish and set aside.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add flour mixture and eggs alternately to creamed mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased Bundt pan and put in cold oven.
Bake at 275° until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.

title: yummy squares
directions: Layer crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil sugar, milk, margarine and graham crackers for 5 minutes.
Pour over crackers while mixture is hot.
Layer another layer of crackers over mixture.
Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips. Pour over crackers.
Spread.
Let cool and allow to set.
May refrigerate for quick set.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch greased dish, brown sausage and drain off grease.
Trim bread and cut into 1/4 inch cubes; spread on bottom of glass baking dish.
Top with sausage.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over sausage.
Top with cheese.
Store, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: u.s. house of representatives bean soup
directions: In a large pot, cover beans with cold water and soak overnight.
Drain and cover with water again.
Add ham hock and simmer slowly for about 4 hours or until beans are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Just before serving, bruise beans with a large spoon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: good ole fudge
directions: Melt candy over low heat until melted, then stir in pecans. Pour into long cake pan.
When cool, cut into squares and serve.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream the butter, oil and sugar.
Add the eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Mix well.
Combine the dry ingredients.
Stir into butter mixture.
Add the Zucchini and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Top with 1/2 c. chocolate chips and 1/4 c. sugar.
Bake 325° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Put onion in a microwavable casserole, covered, and microwave on High for 2 minutes.

title: new southern cracklin' bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
In medium mixing bowl, combine cornmeal, eggs, corn, sour cream, cracklin', oil, and salt.
Mix together well using wire whip or spatula.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan or dish.
Bake 30-40 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from oven and cool or 5 minutes before cutting into pieces. Carefully lift out with spatula onto hot serving platter.
Serves 10-12.

title: cranberry jelly
directions: Cook berries in water until all pop and are soft.
Strain and mash through colander.
Add sugar and boil hard for about 5 minutes.
Pour into container and let cool.
Refrigerate after hardening.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup. Add to jello.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Let set.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Put a layer of berries in the bottom of a pan; sprinkle with sugar and dot with butter.
Add thin strips of crust and repeat until all berries are used.
Cook on top of stove over low heat for a few minutes until it boils good.
Put in a moderate oven until the top crust is brown.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour in pie crust and bake at 250° for 45 minutes.

title: my favorite family recipe
directions: Mix together with complete faith in God.
Add 2 tablespoons of wisdom and 1 teaspoonful of good nature for flavor.
Sprinkle with thoughtfulness.
Serves any and all sizes of families.

title: italian-style beans
directions: Prepare and cook green beans, cut into 1-inch pieces, as directed.
Cook beans, onion, olives and dressing, uncovered, over medium heat, just until onion is tender, about 3 minutes. Sprinkle with tomato.

title: baked manicotti(pizza style)
directions: Beat until smooth. Let stand 1/2 hour. Heat skillet or griddle. Put about 3 Tbsp. of batter on pan and roll around until circle. Let cook a few seconds until dry on top, then slide off to table or smooth surface.

title: stupendous spuds
directions: Prepare 12 servings instant potatoes according to package directions.
Stir in sour cream, softened cream cheese and garlic salt.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and sprinkle Cheddar cheese evenly over top.
Bake 1 hour in preheated 375° oven. Serves 10.
Excellent with baked ham or as main course for meatless meal.

title: ripe catsup
directions: Cook down real low.
Keep stirred so it won't stick.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In one bowl, combine zucchini, oil, sugar, eggs and butternut flavoring.
Then mix other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Grease or spray two loaf pans.
Pour batter in.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peach buttermilk soup
directions: Drop peaches into boiling water for no longer than a count of 10.
Peel under cold running water and remove pits.
Puree in a blender or food processor.
Pour into a medium bowl and add the next 6 ingredients.
Stir to blend well.
Place soup in refrigerator for 6 hours or overnight.
While soup is being chilled, also chill the soup cups or bowls.
Garnish with slivered almonds or toasted coconut.

title: apricot casserole
directions: Place 1 layer of apricot halves in buttered casserole dish. Crush the crackers and sprinkle half on top.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar and repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Pour melted margarine over top layers.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes. Great with ham.

title: mama's magic cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Mix cake as directed on package.
Pour cake mix into baking pan.
Spoon on your choice of pie filling.
Make sure top of cake is all covered.
Mix together the sugar and the melted margarine.
Crumble mix evenly over top of pie filling.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: cranberry cooler
directions: Prepare limeade and water in a large pitcher.
Stir in cranberry juice and Tang.
Pour over ice cubes and garnish with a sprig of fresh mint.

title: spicy meat loaf
directions: Mix together ingredients, seasoning with pepper and salt. Form into a loaf on a foil-lined baking pan.
Top with ketchup and picante sauce mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mash Ritz crackers with margarine.
Pour over vegetable mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake ya hoo hillbilly lazy cookies
directions: Mix butter, graham cracker crumbs and peanut butter.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Roll in medium sized balls.
Make thumbprint in center of each ball.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes a bunch!

title: holiday egg nog
directions: Separate egg whites and yolks.
Beat yolks with sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add the whiskey and brandy very slowly.
Add cream and milk, rinsing the cream container with some of the milk. Wash beaters thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add to the mixture.
Cover with aluminum foil and chill.
Sprinkle each cup of egg nog with nutmeg when serving.

title: mama's shrimp creole
directions: Add pepper, celery, bay leaf, salt, pepper, butter and cayenne pepper to the tomatoes.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter; add parsley.
Add this to mixture.
Add shrimp.
Cook until shrimp are pink.
Pour over fluffy hot rice.

title: peanut butter chocolate dessert
directions: Crush 16 cookies; toss with the butter. Press onto the bottom of an ungreased 9 inch square dish. In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, peanut butter and 1 cup confectioners sugar until smooth. Fold in half of the Cool Whip. Spread over crust. Sprinkle with peanut butter cups.

title: creamy cranberry salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce. Strain out juice. Mix juice, water and gelatin. Stir until dissolved. Add lemon juice and chill until slightly thickened. Add mayonnaise and beat with rotary beater until fluffy. Fold in cranberries, apple and pecans. Chill until firm.

title: chicken and succotash skillet
directions: Lightly coat chicken pieces with 1 tablespoon flour.
Melt half of the butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Cook chicken 5 to 7 minutes, turning once until lightly golden.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Melt remaining butter.
Add onion; cook 4 minutes.
Add bell pepper.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until onion is translucent and pepper is crisp-tender.
Add remaining flour. Cook 2 minutes or until frothy.
Stir in broth, milk and salt. Bring to a boil.
Stir in corn and lima beans.
Simmer 6 to 8 minutes or until sauce is thickened and vegetables are tender. Stir in chicken and tomato.
Cook 1 minute longer to heat through. Serve with warm biscuits.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, brown meat, onion and pepper; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and taco mix.
Set aside. Separate dough and place triangles in ungreased 10-inch pie pan or 9-inch square pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust. Sprinkle corn meal over crust.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes (crust will be puffy when removed from oven).
Spoon meat mixture over corn meal.
Spread sour cream over meat and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: potato soup with dumplings
directions: Cover with water and boil.

title: cherry ice cream
directions: Beat all ingredients together except for the cherries. Add cherries with juice. Freeze in gallon freezer.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix soups, egg, crackers and milk together.
Add hamburg and salt and pepper.
Save a little tomato soup for top of loaf.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy poppy  seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend above ingredients and beat at high speed for a few minutes.
Pour batter into tube pan and bake 50 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini me yaurti
directions: Saute onions and zucchini in olive oil for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Cover and cook until zucchini is tender.
Combine last 5 ingredients together and pour over zucchini.
Heat and serve immediately.

title: mountain mama mudslide cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix and cook all but egg whites on top of stove until it begins to thicken.
Pour into unbaked pie shells, place in oven at 425° and bake for approximately 25 minutes.
Bake until pie shell is done.
Sweeten egg whites and beat into meringue.
Put on top of pies and brown.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate over low heat.
Set off heat and add sugar and evaporated milk.
Mix well and cook over medium heat until it boils.
Serve hot over ice cream, cake, etc.

title: potatoes presto
directions: Place potatoes and 2 tablespoons water in a 1 1/2-quart casserole; cover.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients; microwave on High 2 to 4 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring after 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: reese's cup bars
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and press into a large cookie sheet.
Melt the other stick oleo and chips and pour on top of first mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: spoon bread
directions: Gradually add corn meal to milk while beating.
Stir until it thickens.
Remove from fire and cool slightly.
Add sugar, salt and butter.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in egg whites.
Place in a greased casserole. Bake at 275° for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown on top.
Serve immediately with melted butter.

title: four-layer chocolate pie
directions: Combine margarine, flour and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside. Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended. Stir in zucchini and pecans. Add dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 1-pound coffee cans. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Mix bananas, sugar and buttermilk. Fold in Cool Whip and cherries. Pour into 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch dish and freeze. Remove from the freezer about 15 minutes before serving. Cut into squares and serve.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: Bring sugar, margarine, milk and salt to a boil.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and chocolate chips.
Beat until chips are dissolved.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into glass pie plate or bowls.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: christmas gingersnaps
directions: Bring water, syrup and sugar to the boiling point.
Add butter and stir occasionally until butter is melted.
Chill.
Add spices and baking soda mixed with small amount of flour.
Gradually stir in flour until dough is very soft.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Turn dough onto baking board and work until smooth. Roll out dough, thin, using pastry cloth and cut out cookies with round or fancy cutters.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake in hot oven (400°) 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool before removing to rack. Decorate, if desired, with icing (1/2 cup powdered sugar and 1/2 egg whites, beaten together until smooth) forced through fine paper tube.

title: praline graham
directions: Line a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet with foil.
Break the crackers at indentations.
Place in single layer on pan.
In small saucepan combine oleo and brown sugar.
Bring to a rolling boil over medium heat.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: macaroni (with chipped beef)
directions: Put cooked macaroni in a butter or margarine lined baking dish.

title: quail deluxe
directions: Saute quail in butter for 10 minutes; remove quail.
Add onion and celery to butter and cook 5 minutes over medium heat. Dissolve cornstarch in bouillon; stir into onion-celery mixture and cook until thickened.
Stir in sherry and parsley.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Arrange quail in shallow pan.
Cover with sauce and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: fudgie brownie
directions: Melt butter; stir in cocoa, add sugar, flour , vanilla, salt, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
This can be mixed in same pan that you melt the butter in.

title: white chili
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and heat until cheese is melted.

title: pasta and vegetables
directions: Saute
vegetables
in 1/4 cup olive oil and seasonings. While veggies
are
cooking,
boil
spaghetti.
When both are done,
mix vegetables into drained spaghetti and add other 1/4 cup olive oil. Toss and serve.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix like pie crust and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Thoroughly mix margarine, sugar and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk. Mix together dry ingredients and add to batter.
Stir in nuts, cherries and dates.
Chill dough 1 hour or overnight.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Store tightly covered.

title: lemon congealed salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup cold water and set aside.
Heat pineapple with 1/2 cup sugar and bring to a boil.
Mix with jello mixture. Chill until thickened.
Mix Cool Whip with grated cheese and mix with thickened jello and pineapple mixture.

title: turkey salad
directions: First Layer:
3/4 head lettuce, broken up on bottom.

title: spaghetti slaw
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and cool.
Mix spaghetti, onion, salt, green pepper and cabbage in large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and milk to make dressing.
Pour over spaghetti cabbage mixture and refrigerate until chilled.

title: yankee franks 'n noodles
directions: In a skillet brown frankfurters and cook with seasoning in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and tomatoes.
Add noodles and parsley.
Heat. Stir now and then.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in margarine until transparent; add remaining ingredients except cheese and noodles. Simmer 20 minutes.
Spoon enough of mixture to cover bottom of 8 x 11-inch pan.
Cover with uncooked noodles.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 4 servings; 3 protein, 1 bread and 2 vegetables.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together and freeze before serving.

title: gum candy cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until light.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with applesauce.
Add nuts and raisins and cut up gum candy slices. Bake 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven in greased, paper lined pans.
Fill pans not more than two-thirds full.

title: turtle pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small heavy saucepan, slowly melt caramels with 1/3 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Spread evenly on bottom of pie shell.
In medium saucepan, slowly melt chocolate with margarine.
In large bowl, beat eggs with remaining condensed milk, water, vanilla and salt.
Add chocolate mixture; mix well. Pour into pastry shell.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bake 35 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Line large baking dish with vanilla wafers. Add, in layers, bananas, pineapple and condensed milk with lemon juice, whipped cream (tinted, if desired), flaked coconut, nuts and cherries. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: sparkling lemon ice
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add drink, lemon juice and peel.
Pour into an 8 to 9-inch square pan; cover.
Freeze about 3 hours.
Remove from freezer; let stand about 10 minutes.
Beat at medium speed.
Scoop into individual dishes.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Cook turkey, onions and garlic until meat is brown; drain fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, basil and oregano.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms.

title: hot seafood salad casserole
directions: Cook chopped celery, finely chopped onion and finely chopped green pepper in butter (1 tablespoon) for 15 minutes.
In a saucepan, melt 1/4 cup butter.
Add the flour, milk, mayonnaise, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper. Cook slowly until creamy, stirring constantly.
Add the cooked vegetables, shrimp, crab, tuna and mushrooms.
Line a buttered dish, 7 x 11-inch, with 1 cup cooked rice.
Pour in the mixture.
Cover with buttered crumbs. Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in cupcake pan with paper cupcake liners.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes and remove from paper liners.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine until lightly browned.
Add broth, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer 20 minutes. Sprinkle toast with Parmesan cheese, place under broiler a few seconds until cheese is browned.
Cut each slice into 3 pieces. Pour soup in bowls and float toast slices on top.

title: rice dressing
directions: Season meat with Tony's Creole seasoning and garlic powder. Turn meat on high.
Add chopped pepper and celery.
Brown meat until sticks to the bottom.
Pour about 2 cups of water to make gravy.
Add onion soup.
Heat until boiling.
Add raw rice and green onions.
Turn on low fire and cook until done, stirring occasionally.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: date cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Pour boiling water over dates, cut fine.
Add soda.
Add to sugar and egg mixture.
Add flour with baking powder.
Batter is thin.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; make small balls.
Put a little chocolate in bottom of paper cup, then place the peanut ball and pour more chocolate over top.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat margarine, butter and cream cheese (at room temperature). Add eggs, sugar, salt and flour.
Cream together.
Bake in cold oven for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: dunking doughnuts
directions: In a large bowl, combine, in the order listed, all ingredients except the oil.
Stir well and turn out on a floured board. Flatten the dough to about 5/8-inch thick.
Cut out doughnuts with doughnut cutter or glass.
Drop the doughnuts into hot oil until brown on one side.
Turn and brown the other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Roll in powdered sugar or sugar cinnamon mixture.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
In a greased casserole, place alternate layers of potatoes and onions.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Place pork chops on top and pour cream of mushroom soup over all.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers.
Slice cucumbers the thickness of a dime. Place sliced cucumbers in a bowl and sprinkle with 2 teaspoons of salt and allow to stand for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt into a 1 1/2-quart saucepan. Stir in milk gradually.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir at least half of the flaked coconut gradually into egg yolks.
Blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle top with 1/4 cup flaked coconut.

title: mushroom baked sole
directions: Saute	onion,	parsley
and
mushrooms
in
margarine, stirring
constantly
until
onion	is
soft.
Place
half the fillets
in
a
buttered
baking
dish.
Sprinkle lightly with pepper
and spread sauteed mixture evenly over fish.
Top with any remaining	fillets;
season
with pepper.	Pour wine over all. Bake
at
350° uncovered for 15 minutes (slightly longer if fillets are not thin).
Remove from oven and drain, reserving the pan
liquids.
In
a small saucepan combine flour and milk; add the reserved pan liquid and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.	Pour
over
the fish and bake 5 minutes longer. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: tortilla skillet
directions: Cut tortillas into thin strips.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet until hot.
Cook tortillas and onions, turning occasionally until tortillas are crisp, about 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese; heat just until cheese is melted.
Serve with sour cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato saute and sausage or turkey
directions: Cut each unpeeled potato into quarters and cut stem end from beans.
In 6-quart pan, heat potatoes covered in hot water to boiling over high heat.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 7 minutes.
Stir in green beans, adding more hot water if needed. Bring to a boil over high heat, reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain.
Thinly slice onions.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, put 1 1/2 tablespoons hot salad oil and cook sausage until lightly brown.
Add onions and continue cooking until onions are tender.
Stir in 1/2 cup water, turn heat to low; cover and cook until sausage is cooked through.
Remove sausage mixture to bowl.
In same skillet, in 1 1/2 tablespoons hot salad oil, cook potatoes and green beans with salt and pepper until potatoes are golden, stirring frequently. Cut tomatoes in wedges.
Return sausage mixture to skillet, then add tomatoes and heat through. Spoon on to warm platters.
Makes 8 main dish servings.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil together.
Combine flour with baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Gradually add this mixture to egg mixture; knead.
Add raisins, nuts and apples.
Spread into square or 9 x 13-inch oblong form.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle lightly with fine sugar.

title: calico casserole
directions: Line a greased 9 x 12 baking dish with potatoes; add a layer of corned beef.
Cover with onions, then sliced eggs.
Add seasonings.
Cover with sauce, then a thin layer of bread crumbs, mixed with an equal amount of cheese.
Dust with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons flour and 2 tablespoons sugar; sprinkle over chilled pie shell.
Pile cut rhubarb over this and sprinkle with mixture of remaining flour and sugar, varying amount of sugar, according to taste.
Dot with butter.
Top with chilled crust and seal; slit top crust to vent.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake for 35 minutes.

title: i fought the slaw and the slaw won
directions: Shred cabbage, chopped celery, onion, pepper and carrots. Sprinkle with sugar and mix well.
Bring vinegar, oil, celery seed and salt to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture and chill overnight.

title: rolls
directions: Mix egg, sugar, salt, oil and water.
Add yeast and mix.
Add flour.
Cover and let rise for 2 hours.
Roll and let rise until double.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; add to salad, mix and serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Gradually, with fingers, work flour into sausage.
When all flour has been well mixed with sausage, gradually work cheese into mixture.
(If desired, sprinkle a few drops of Tabasco sauce into mixture.)
Roll into balls about 1 inch.
Place on greased baking pan and chill about 1 hour.
Bake in 400° oven until golden brown. Place on paper towels to get rid of excess drippings.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: chicken and corn bread dressing casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken well.
Pour into a buttered baking dish.
Remove bones from chicken and lay on top of dressing.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until lightly brown, but soft.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour large cookie sheet. In a small bowl, mix on high speed egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Add sugar.
Beat on high speed, adding 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition, until sugar is dissolved.
Beat in vanilla.
(Whites should stand in glossy peaks.)
With rubber spatula, fold in coconut and flour.
Drop coconut by level tablespoons 1 inch apart.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Store tightly in container.

title: michelle gipson's bierrox(stuffed cabbage)
directions: (Double recipe and freeze extra.)

title: danish apple cake
directions: Melt oleo in a skillet.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Gently brown. Add brown sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Alternate layers of crumbs with applesauce.
Begin and end with crumbs.
Press crumbs down gently.
Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream (or not)!

title: spanish sangria
directions: Fill large pitcher with a couple of trays of ice and add the ingredients in the following order:
sugar, brandy, fruits, chilled wine and chilled club soda.
Mix with spoon and serve in old-fashion glasses.
A delicious summer drink.
Serves 2 if you're thirsty, 4 if you're not.

title: punch
directions: Mix together.
Add ginger ale right before serving.
Serves 50.

title: sausage-wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, set aside.
Brown sausage in a skillet stirring to crumble; drain well.
Combine cooked rice, sausage and remaining ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2 quart casserole.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients
together.
Add
shortening. Dissolve yeast
in	warm
water and add with buttermilk to dry ingredients; mix
well.
Turn
out on floured board;
add more flour if
necessary and roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut; then dip in melted butter and fold to make pocketbook rolls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Beat butter and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed until well blended. Beat in eggs and vanilla.

title: biryani
directions: Marinate meat or chicken in thick yogurt for 1/2 hour.
Fry clove, cinnamon and cardamon in oil.
Add slit green chillies and onion.
Fry until onion is well cooked, then add mint, cilantro, ginger and garlic paste and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder.
Fry well.
Add salt (to taste) and meat with curds; cook for 20 minutes (lid closed).
Add rice and twice the quantity of water.
(If rice is 1 cup, then add 2 cups of water.)
Cook for 5 minutes on high flame in open container.
Reduce flame, close container and cook for 5 minutes.
Open after 20 minutes and it is ready to be served.

title: fruit bars
directions: Mix all but last 2 ingredients at once, real well.
Spread over an 18 x 12-inch cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with coconut and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: batter way rolls
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in bowl.
Mix water and yeast good, add egg and shortening, then mix with dry ingredients.
Let stand 1 hour.
Shape in pan and let rise 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Brush with butter and put back in oven 1 minute.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix cheese with cream.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt. Add chopped nuts, pineapple and fruit cocktail to cheese mixture. Add whipping cream.
Freeze without stirring.
Serve with pecans and mayonnaise.

title: candied apple
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan; bring to boil.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes, covered.
Take cover off, reduce heat and cook down low. (Recipe for 2 apples, double for 4 apples.)

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Divide nuts and chips in bottom of 2 unbaked pie shells.
Mix butter, eggs, sugar and syrup together.
Pour into pie shells. Bake 30-40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: ratatouille
directions: Combine everything except tomatoes in frying pan. Cook over low heat for 10 minutes. Add tomatoes. This can be served hot or cold. Serves 6.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Soak for 1 hour in ice water and then drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar and salt.
Pour over well drained cucumbers.
Refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: mama's chocolate pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar, milk, flour, cocoa and vanilla in a boiler and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread beans in baking dish.
Cover with cream cheese, then salsa, and top with cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Dip with your favorite chips.

title: chewy chocolate chip oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 2 large cookie sheets with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl, beat on low speed corn oil, brown sugar and sugar until combined.
Increase speed to high. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg whites, egg and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
With spoon, stir in flour, oats, chocolate pieces, raisins, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Drop dough by level tablespoons on cookie sheet.
Bake cookies 10 to 12 minutes until golden.
Remove cookies with pancake turner.
Place on wire rack to cool.
Repeat until all batter is used.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Mix about 4 ounces beef with all other ingredients, using enough sour cream to form a soft ball.
Roll ball in remaining chipped beef and serve with bacon flavored crackers.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In a large pot, boil cabbage and onions (cut up both as if frying) in lightly salted water until cabbage is tender.
In casserole dish, cut up cheese and margarine (just as if fixing macaroni and cheese).
When cabbage is tender, drain off water and put hot cabbage in dish with cheese and margarine until cheese is good and stringy.
Then add pepper, milk, eggs and the Worcestershire sauce.
Stir well and bake in preheated oven at 350° until a golden brown on top.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: tiger candy
directions: In a regular pot, melt on low heat the peanut butter and white chocolate.
Spread wax paper on a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cookie sheet. Then spread melted mixture.
Melt chocolate chips, then swirl with knife.
When you add dark chocolate, put in dots all over white chocolate mixture, then with butter knife, swirl.
Put in refrigerator until hard.
Cut into pieces as big as you like.

title: strawberry vinegar
directions: Fill a jar with rinsed whole strawberries (do not hull).
Cover with vinegar and seal.
Refrigerate for 10 days.
Strain and measure vinegar; discard berries.
For each pint of vinegar, add 3 cups sugar.
Bring mixture to a boil; boil 2 minutes.
Cool.
Pour into sterile bottles or jars; seal.
Use as a base for salad dressings.
Perfect for holiday gifts, too.

title: favorite apple pie(tart)
directions: Make crust.
Make
layer
of
apples;
spread flour and sugar over.
Melt margarine.
Drizzle over top.
Bake either 2 crust or single crust pie at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook chuck roast and water overnight in crock-pot on high until falling apart.
Let cool and remove all fat.
Shred beef and return to crock-pot using 2 cups of liquid the beef was cooked in.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain off fat.
Add ground beef and remaining ingredients to shredded beef mixing thoroughly.
Cook on high 4 to 5 hours.
Serve on buns.
Makes 24 sandwiches.

title: shirley's baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in foil-lined baking pan.
Cut up onions, carrots and potatoes on top of chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves about 6.

title: irish bread
directions: *Must use self-rising flour.

title: chickpea salad
directions: Combine peas, onion, parsley, pimiento and garlic; toss lightly.
Add dressing and stir.
Allow to marinate 4 hours.

title: pizza
directions: Spread dough on a pan.
Mix the sauce and seasonings.
Spread the sauce over the dough.
Take the cheese and put it over the sauce, then put all the toppings you want on top of the cheese. Put in the oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hanky pankys
directions: Brown meats; drain.
Add remaining ingredients to meat; stir until cheese is melted.
Spread on bread.
May bag and freeze. Broil 3 or 4 minutes.

title: broiled venison steaks
directions: Place steaks on broiler pan.
Season with meat tenderizer.
In small pan melt 1 to 2 sticks margarine, depending on number of steaks; 1 stick will do about 4 medium steaks.
Mix seasonings into melted margarine.
Brush tops of steaks with mixture and place under broiler.
Keep steaks brushed with mixture as they brown.
Do the same with other side.
Do not overcook.
This mixture works great when you grill as well.

title: chicken-rice casserole (or turkey)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt chicken fat in large saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients and mix by hand. Do not use electric mixer. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Spread topping over cake while warm.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Use a glass or stone crock for the best results.
Combine the sugar, flour and salt; mix well.
Add the water and beat mixture to a smooth batter.
Add the vinegar.
Place in a warm place overnight.
You determine when starter is ready by the yeasty smell.
Store it in a refrigerator until ready to use.
If it is not to be used for several weeks, it should be frozen or dried to prevent spoiling.
This starter gathers yeast from the air to provide leavening.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine sugar, milk and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Add pecans and cook to 236° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.

Without stirring, add butter, then let stand 5 minutes. Add vanilla and stir until slightly thick and syrup begins to look cloudy. Drop quickly by spoonfuls onto buttered cookie sheet or waxed paper. Allow to cool thoroughly.

title: oatmeal-raisin scoties
directions: Cover raisins with water; cook and cool overnight.
Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Then add 8 tablespoons juice off raisins and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix together flour, cinnamon, baking powder, salt and soda.
Then add to first mixture and mix well.
Last, add raisins (drained) and oatmeal.

title: potato chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredient together until creamy.
Use as dip for potato chips.

title: water chestnut appetizers
directions: Mix until dissolved sugar, mayo and sauce.
Drain water chestnuts.
Cut bacon into 3 pieces.
Wrap bacon around chestnut slices and secure with a toothpick.
Cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Fit pastry into 9-inch pie pan and prick generously with fork. Bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Line baked pastry shell with 3 cups strawberries.
Simmer 1 cup strawberries and 3/4 cup water in saucepan about 3 to 4 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and sugar; add to cooked fruit.
Cook until syrup is thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice and red food coloring; cook slightly.
Pour over berries in pastry shell. Chill thoroughly.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: hearty tuscan soup(makes 4 servings)
directions: In a large saucepan, over medium heat, heat oil. Add onion and garlic. Cook about 3 minutes. Add broth and tomatoes; bring to a boil. Add pierogies and return to boil; boil 4 minutes. Add beans, spinach and cumin; return to boil. Reduce heat and simmer until spinach is tender. Serve with cheese and crushed red pepper. I usually add a teaspoon of dried oregano and dried basil to this soup.

title: franks a lot
directions: Cut up franks into 1/2-inch slices. Add with pepper and onion to tomato sauce and simmer for 15 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, to cook ingredients.

title: pinwheel meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, half of processed Cheez Whiz spread, egg and salt; mix lightly.
Pat out meat mixture to cover 12 x 10-inch rectangle of foil.
Combine remaining cheese, rice and parsley; spread over meat.
Roll up, starting at narrow end.
Wrap securely; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Cut roll into 8 slices; place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until meat is done.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Layer half of the oysters in casserole. Top with half of the crackers and pour half of melted butter over.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: egg casserole
directions: Press biscuits, croissants or bread into bottom of baking dish.
Place browned sausage on top of it, then egg mixture (mix eggs as you would for scrambled eggs).
Top with cheese, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ric's grilled tilapia
directions: You will also need aluminum foil for grilling.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar; mix thoroughly.
Add eggs one at a time.
Then add flour, one cup at a time.
Add flavorings and 7-Up; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in pan for 30 minutes, then take out.

title: autumn soup
directions: Brown the hamburger and chopped onion.
Add carrots, celery, potatoes, water, salt, bouquet sauce, bay leaf and pepper.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer.
Cook, covered, for 20 minutes. Add stewed tomatoes and simmer for 10 minutes more.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Add broccoli to boiling water.
Boil for 10 minutes on medium-high.
Add salt, margarine and milk.
Slowly add potato flakes to thicken.
Add grated cheese to flavor (optional).

title: twenty-four hour cabbage slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion, green pepper, olives and sugar. Combine remaining ingredients; boil for 3 minutes.
Pour hot dressing over cabbage mixture.
Cover and chill for 24 hours. Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: lynn's secret barbecue sauce
directions: Heat sugar, catsup, water and Worcestershire sauce and vinegar in saucepan until it strikes a boil.
Mix together pepper, mustard, chili powder, garlic and salt and rub into the meat (chicken, beef, ribs, etc.).
Bake or grill 1/2 hour, then start basting with catsup mix until you use all the mix.
Grill and eat.

title: rocks
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well; add remaining ingredients.
Then add enough flour so that mixture will drop from spoon in size you want.
Bake at 350° to 375° for about 10 minutes or until desired brownness.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: old fashioned cherry pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine sugar, flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Stir in juice.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick; cook 1 minute longer.
Add cherries, butter, extract and 10 drops of red food coloring.
Let stand.
Make pastry.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first
3 ingredients together and let simmer for 45 minutes.
With
ground
beef,
form meatballs and cook in oven until done.
Serve after letting meatballs simmer in sauce.

title: raspberry swirl cheesecake pie
directions: Line pie shell with double thickness of tin foil.
Bake at 450 for 5 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake 5 more minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce heat to 350.
In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Add eggs beating on low, until just combined.
Pour into crust.
Stir jam.
Drizzle over filling.
Cut through with knife to swirl.
Bake 25-30 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool on wire rack 1 hour. Refrigerate overnight.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before slicing.
Pipe cool whip around pie if desired.

title: mrs. shafer's chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and coffee.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 1 minute more.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) cake tins. Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Combine 1 cup blueberries, sugar and water in saucepan.
Mix cornstarch with a little of the water; stir until a smooth paste. Add to pan.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat; add lemon juice, butter and jello.
Stir; let cool.
Pour over remaining 3 cups of berries in baked pie shell.
Chill several hours and garnish with whipped topping.

title: chicken divan
directions: In shallow casserole, arrange broccoli.
Top with chicken. Combine soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Combine margarine and bread crumbs; sprinkle over top.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add shortening, buttermilk and bananas.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and nuts.
Beat 2 minutes. Mix altogether.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Fry hamburger meat and onion together (fine) until brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add altogether and simmer in crock-pot. Serve with corn bread.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Combine flour, buttermilk, oil, soda and salt in a large bowl which has a tight-fitting cover.
Mix thoroughly.
Combine water, sugar and yeast.
Add the flour mixture, mixing thoroughly again. Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
To make biscuits, pinch off amount of dough needed and knead on a lightly floured board.
Roll out to desired thickness and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Bake lightly greased pan at 450° until golden brown. This dough will keep for about 25 days in the refrigerator.
Makes about 3 dozen biscuits.

title: smoked ham with hot black bean sauce
directions: Place ham hocks in
a pot, cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat
and
simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Heat another pan with
vegetable
oil,
when
oil
is hot, add black beans, chopped garlic, mash and crush them well together.
Stir in ham hocks,
sliced
green
pepper, soy sauce, red hot pepper and chicken broth.
Stir
until
blended.
Add green onions and salt. Serve hot.
Finger lickin good.

title: rye bowl dip
directions: Defrost shrimp.
Remove shell and vein.
Place shrimp in boiling water with bay leaf and lemon.
Cook until it comes to a boil.
Pour off water and place shrimp in ice water.

title: "philadelphia cream cheese ball"
directions: Mix cream cheese, chopped ham, cayenne pepper and diced green pepper well.
I use my hands.
Shape into a ball and roll in bacon bits until covered.
Chill and serve with Wheat Thins.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Combine soy sauce, sugar, butter, mustard and Sauterne in saucepan; stir until melted.
Spread wings in baking pan.
Pour hot mixture over wings.
Marinate for 1 hour in refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn once after 30 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Beat sugar with cream cheese; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix together remaining ingredients.
Add cream cheese mixture.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Garnish with nuts (optional) and freeze.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter; add flour and seasonings.
Add milk slowly! Cook until sauce thickens.
Add sliced potatoes and pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dottie's leftover kielbasa gumbo
directions: In large Dutch oven or crock-pot, combine ingredients and 5 cups of water.
Cover and simmer 1 /2 hours or equal time in crock-pot until tender.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: caramel orange ring
directions: Grease 12 cup Bundt or tube pan with 1 tablespoon butter.
Put teaspoonfuls of marmalade in pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon in small bowl; set aside.
Separate biscuits and dip each in melted butter, then in sugar mixture.
Stand biscuits on edge in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar and drizzle on the remaining butter.
Cool upright in pan for 5 minutes.
Invert on serving plate.

title: orange dream soda
directions: Evenly scoop ice cream into 4 tall glasses.
Fill each with orange soda.
Serve with licorice stick as a straw.
Great for Halloween.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn souffle
directions: Add cheese, flour, sugar and other seasonings to corn.
Mix well.
Beat egg.
Add to corn.
Heat milk and add to mixture. Pour into baking dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about an hour or until firm.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Combine all ingredients except onions.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and top with French fried onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and cornstarch.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add milk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Pour in pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; turn oven to 325° and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large saucepan, brown ground beef; drain.
Add garlic, parsley, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, pepper, parsley flakes and Parmesan cheese.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Spread a thin layer of the tomato sauce in the bottom of pan. Place a layer of noodles in dish; spread 1/2 the cottage cheese mixture over noodles.
Layer with 1/2 the Mozzarella; top with 1/2 the sauce mixture.
Repeat process, topping with noodles and covering with sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
Freezes (before baking) well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Note:
Amount of ingredients may be varied according to number of servings desired.

title: massachusetts bay company chowder
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Saute leeks, onion, celery and scallions until soft.
Blend in flour and cook for 5 minutes. While stirring, add stock and clam juice; simmer for 30 minutes. Stir in cream, wine, clams, potatoes and tarragon.
Gently simmer for 10 minutes.
Season to taste.
Makes 10 servings.

title: shepherd's pie or scalloped meat
directions: It is unnecessary to follow ingredient proportions.
Use available amounts of meat, potato and gravy.
Season to taste. Line bottom of buttered baking dish with well beaten mashed potatoes (either hor or leftover).
Add thick layer of meat and gravy, then layer of potatoes, until dish is full.
Make the top crust of potatoes.
Dot with bits of butter.
Or, meat and gravy may be placed in lower part of baking dish with single thick layer of mashed potatoes for the crust.

Stiffly beaten egg white may be folded into mashed potatoes before adding to meat, if desired. Bake in hot oven until potatoes are brown or if cold potatoes have been used, until thoroughly heated and browned.
Crumbs, macaroni or rice may be substituted for potatoes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Then add sugar, one cup at a time while still beating.
Mixture will become thick and creamy.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Pour sugar, syrup and water in a pan.
Boil until it spins a thread or forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat, then fold in a little of the egg whites.
Repeat until you have used all the egg whites.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts, if desired.
Beat until mixture becomes stiff.
Pour into greased pan or dish immediately.
Garnish with walnuts, if desired.
Cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Blend cinnamon and sugar; shake biscuits in this mixture.
Layer in greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter; blend with sugar and vanilla.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Can be cut into third and baked in single layer cake pan.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Shape into balls and flatten with fork on top with a Hershey's Kiss. Bake at 350°F for 12-15 min.
Makes about 1 doz.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, milk and coconut in blender. Fold in one 8 ounce Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust and freeze 4 hours.

title: macaroni pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in shortening.
Pour off excess grease.
Add soup and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes or until thick.
Cook macaroni; beat eggs and milk.
Add to drained macaroni.
Spread in a buttered dish.
Top with meat sauce, then sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chocaroon bundt cake
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
