Gradually add sugar and beat until mixture forms stiff shiny peaks.
Blend in flour and coconut; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in large mixer bowl. Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour 1/3 of batter into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Spoon in coconut mixture and top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan about 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on a rack.
Top with glaze.

title: ky. cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Grease skillet or pan; place in oven to heat.
Mix meal, flour and milk and add enough water to batter so batter will pour easily.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.

title: crumbled apple dessert
directions: Slice
apples
in deep baking dish.
Cover with 2/3 cup brown sugar,
cinnamon
and butter.
Sprinkle cold water over all. Combine
cup brown sugar, flour, 1/2 cup butter and salt to form
a crumbly mixture.
Put on top of apples.
Bake for 30
to 40
minutes or until apples are tender and crust a golden brown.

title: edna's brownie pie
directions: Melt butter in microwave.
Combine other items in order in same pan.
Pour into buttered pie pan (no crust).
Sprinkle with chopped pecans, if desired.
Bake at 300° for 28 to 30 minutes. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: butterhorns
directions: Cream butter and cheese together with mixer until blended; beat in salt and flour until smooth.
Cover; refrigerate 4 hours. Divide into 3 parts; form into balls.
On lightly floured surface, roll out flat into circles 12 inches in diameter.
Cut into 12 pie-shaped wedges.
Roll each wedge from wide to small end.
Place on greased cookie sheet with tips turned under.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
While butterhorns bake, mix remaining ingredients.
Spread over tops.
Cool completely.

title: seven layer cookie
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 11 1/2-inch pan.
Add remaining ingredients in order given, evenly making layers of each.
Bake 1/2 hour in a 350° oven.
Let cool thoroughly.
Cut in 2-inch squares while still in pan.

title: charlie's venison steak roll
directions: Mix stuffing well and place on steak. Roll and tie securely. Set rolled steak in roast pan and place the bacon strips around the roll. Roast at 325° for about 1 hour, covered. Add 1/2 cup bouillon to the pan and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Use drippings for gravy sauce.

title: lemon-sesame broccoli
directions: Trim flowerets off broccoli; cut into pieces (or leave stems whole).
Peel stems; cut in 1-inch rounds.
Bring 1 inch of water to boiling in large saucepan.
Add stems, cover and cook 5 minutes. Add flowerets, cover and cook 5 minutes more.
If using whole stems, cook 10 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute margarine and onion.
Add dressing mix.
Line 9 x 9-inch pan with this, saving some for the topping.
Mix soup, sour cream and zucchini.
Pour this mixture over dressing mix in pan and put on the topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's famous deer roast
directions: Take front deer shoulder and place in oven roaster bag.
Next, peel and cut the potatoes as desired.
Then peel the onion and cut it in half.
Then cut the carrots into small lengths.
Place potatoes, onions and carrots in oven bag and then add about 1 1/2 to 2 cups of water.
Season as desired.
Close the bag and cook at 200° all night.
This roast will be very tender and tasty.
Enjoy!

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and pour into casserole dish.
Mix flour, milk, egg and sugar together and pour over melted butter.
Pour peaches into mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake for 45 minutes at 425° or until brown.

title: black-eyed skillet dinner
directions: Cook the ground beef, onion, garlic and green pepper over medium heat until beef is browned.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring often.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put in greased casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: quick and easy sausage casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, mushrooms, celery and soup and 1/2 cup cheese.
Spoon into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange sausage on top of potato mixture.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray large nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Heat over high heat until hot.
Add ground beef; brown 8 to 10 minutes or until thoroughly cooked. Drain well; return beef to skillet.
Add beans, tomatoes, chiles and taco seasoning mix; mix well.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes. Meanwhile, spray 12 x 8-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut each tortilla in half; place 6 halves in bottom of sprayed cooking dish, overlapping slightly.
Spoon half of beef mixture evenly over tortillas. Spoon sour cream over beef mixture; spread evenly.
Top with remaining 6 tortilla halves and remaining beef mixture.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; let stand 3 minutes until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with cilantro. Makes 6 servings.

title: fish fillet in wine sauce(microwave recipe)
directions: Put butter and onion in baking dish and microwave on High for 30 seconds.
Lay fillets over the onions and cover with mushrooms, pour wine over top.
Cover baking dish with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 8 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn every few minutes.
Meanwhile, mix flour, salt, cream and pepper; blend until smooth.
Drain the hot liquid from fish into cream mixture and stir well.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove hot liquid from microwave, add 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice to liquid and pour over fish.
Take 3/4 cup of shredded cheese, sprinkle on fish and microwave for 2 minutes on High.

title: layered salad
directions: Put ingredients in a large clear salad bowl in the order given.
Many items are optional.
Smooth mayonnaise on top, completely covering other ingredients.
Top with black pepper. Bacon bits may be added just before serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together, then chill.
Serve with strawberries, apples, pears or bananas.

title: kansas city curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand for several hours or overnight.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Cook broccoli 3 to 4 minutes; drain.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Mix broccoli and ham; place in crust.
Pour egg mixture over broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes more.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, rice, catsup and chili sauce.
Mix well and put into green peppers.
Place in dish.
Add more catsup over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hamburger is brown and pepper is tender.
Salt and pepper.

title: german potato salad
directions: Season potatoes with salt, pepper and onion and set aside. Fry bacon until crisp.
Stir in flour and cook, stirring constantly, for a minute or two.
Add vinegar, water and sugar. Continue cooking and stirring until mixture bubbles.
Pour over potatoes and toss gently.
Tastes best served warm.
Serves 4.

title: quick easy cobbler
directions: Fruit:
Use peaches, apples, cherries or blueberries.

title: broccoli elegant
directions: Combine water, 4 tablespoons butter and seasoning packet from stuffing; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in stuffing crumbs; let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon stuffing around inside edge of lightly buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, leaving well in center.
Place broccoli in well; set aside.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir in bouillon.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Add cream cheese and salt, stirring until smooth.
Stir in onion.
Spoon mixture over center of broccoli.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and paprika. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes; remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: leslie vinkler's barbecue sauce for barbecued beef
directions: Cook onions in oil until soft, then add all ingredients (except last 4 ) and cook (simmer) over charcoal for 30 minutes or more.

title: easy beefy squares
directions: Brown beef with salt and pepper.
Stir in mushrooms and sour cream.
Pat unrolled crescent dough into 9 x 13 pan to form crust. Spoon hot meat mixture over crust.
Top with cheese slices.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until deep golden brown.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: delicious raisin mold
directions: Soak gelatin and water.
Melt together butter, sour cream and cream cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Add gelatin to this mixture. Finally, add sugar, nuts and raisins.
Mold overnight and serve on crackers.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Wash blueberries and drain.
Mix and sift flour with salt, sugar and baking powder.
Beat egg and mix with milk.
Stir egg and milk into the flour mixture.
Add the berries and melted shortening.
Mix well and pour into greased muffin pans filling them 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 9 to 12 muffins.
(Do not overmix the muffins, as it will cause them to tunnel.)

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Add rice, corn and soup. Mix well.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls according to directions after flattening them on a cookie sheet.

title: mexican munch snack
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, combine onions, cereal, peanuts and potato sticks. Melt butter or margarine over low heat; drizzle over mixture in baking pan and stir well. Sprinkle the seasoning mix evenly over mixture, mixing well. Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Allow to cool. Makes about 7 cups.

title: favorite fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan, except fruit; boil until thickened.
Pour while hot over fruit.
This fruit salad will keep well several days and will not darken.

title: harvard beets
directions: In sauce pan heat all of the above except the beets till thickened and then add beets and butter making sure all is heated through.
Very good and adds color to you meal.

title: middle eastern burgers
directions: Combine ground beef, oats, egg, oregano, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape into patties and cook to desired doneness.
Combine yogurt, onion and dill weed and spoon over patties.

title: nutty slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, carrots and onions and set aside.
Brown the almonds and sunflower seeds in the butter.
Set aside to cool. Blend together the Accent, sugar, oil and vinegar until all dissolved. When ready to serve, mix all together and then add the Ramen noodles that have been broken up.

title: creamed noodles
directions: Boil noodles until at your desired tenderness.
In a separate pot, heat soup, milk and tuna until lukewarm.
Finally, mix together and serve.

title: mexican skillet spaghetti
directions: Brown meat.
Add tomato sauce, water, taco mix, and onion. Bring mixture to a boil.
Add spaghetti.
Reduce heat and simmer covered until spaghetti is tender, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: tea cups
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add flour, mix and make 24 small balls out of mixture.
Press balls into ungreased mini muffin pan, forming a cup, in each.
Mix together last 4 ingredients and place 1 teaspoon into each muffin cup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: adeline's baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions and drain.
Shred cheese and stir in hot macaroni until all is melted.
Stir in margarine. Add eggs, one at a time and mix thoroughly.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Season to taste with salt.
Bake at 325° for approximately 40 minutes or until custard is set.
(Take care not to overbake.)

title: my layered salad
directions: First Layer:
Wash, drain and chop lettuce.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy, 12 to 13 for crisp cookies.

title: smothered steak
directions: Cut
steak
into
serving portions.
Salt and pepper to taste. Roll
in flour.
Sprinkle paprika on each side.
Brown in margarine.	When
all
the steak is browned on both sides, remove from skillet.
Wash skillet.
Brown onion in 1/2 stick of margarine.	Add steak to skillet after sprinkling each side with a
small amount of soy sauce.
Cover.
Cook on low for 1 hour.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and drain excess fat.
Add sauce, water, seasoning and sugar. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs.
Add flour, nutmeg and cinnamon; stir.
Add vanilla, coconut, pecans and apples.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 375° for about an hour.

title: beef jerky
directions: Partially freeze a 3 pound piece of lean beef for easier slicing.
Slice thin (1/4-inch thick) in long strips.
Remove all fat as you slice (or it will taste rancid).

title: corn salad
directions: Combine corn, cucumber, onion and tomatoes in salad bowl. Blend sour cream with mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Add sour cream mixture to corn mixture.
Toss to coat vegetables. Chill thoroughly.
Spoon onto lettuce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Heat these ingredients together.
Mix together and let stand a couple of days.

title: pecan butter balls
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Add margarine and vanilla and mix well.
Add nuts.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Roll in powdered sugar and place on wax paper to cool.

title: crawfish jambalaya in rice cooker
directions: Spray
rice cooker with Pam.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well. Cook
until
rice is done.
Fluff with fork.
Jambalaya can be cooked in Dutch oven, on stove as you would cook rice.

title: creamy broccoli and ham
directions: Melt margarine.
Cook broccoli, ham, celery, peas, carrots, onion, salt, marjoram and pepper for 10 minutes.
Stir in mayonnaise and milk.
Add cheese.
Cook until it melts.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cook a little longer, if needed.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Mix catsup, brown sugar, vinegar and garlic powder together. Reserve one-half of catsup mixture and set aside to be sued later on top of loaf.
Combine bread crumbs and 1/2 catsup mixture.
Add onion, green pepper, salt, black pepper, egg, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce; mix well.
Add one teaspoon catsup mixture to bread crumb mixture to moisten; let stand for a few minutes for flavors to blend.
Add turkey and place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole or greased 9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Pack mixture and spread the reserved catsup mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand in pan for a few minutes before slicing and serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Blend the first four ingredients.
Add butter, egg and pineapple.
Drop mixture from spoon onto cookie sheet.
Top with mixture of 1/2 teaspoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: ribbon pasta with vegetables
directions: Add egg noodles to boiling, salted water along with the 2 teaspoons of vegetable oil.
Stir occasionally.
Cook for 4 minutes.
Add the snow peas or vegetables.
Bring to a boil again. Boil 2 to 3 minutes longer or until
pasta is tender, but still firm to the bite and the snow peas or vegetables are brightly colored.
Drain snow peas, vegetables and pasta.
Rinse with hot water.
Add oil, butter and garlic to the pan in which the pasta was cooked.
Heat 1 minute.
Add drained pasta and snow peas or vegetables to the garlic mixture in the pot.
Toss until pasta is coated with the garlic butter.
Serve immediately with Parmesan cheese sprinkled over all.

title: irresistible kool dessert
directions: Place ice cream sandwiches in a shallow dish. Cover with about an inch of Cool Whip. Drizzle caramel topping over Cool Whip. Sprinkle Toffee Bits on top. Freeze. Remove from freezer and serve.

title: cool cherry jello surprise
directions: Prepare cake according to the normal directions and bake. While the cake is still warm, prepare Jell-O, using 1 cup of boiling water and 1 cup of ice cubes.
With a meat fork, punch holes in cake and pour Jell-O over cake.
Cool the cake.
After cooling, spread Cool Whip over cake and top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: sweet milk doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs; add slowly, beating constantly, the sugar, then stir in the milk, shortening, sifted flour, resifted with baking powder, cinnamon or lemon rind and salt.
Add 1/4 teaspoon of nutmeg (if desired).
Mix moist and dry ingredients.

title: crabbies
directions: Mix ingredients. Cut muffins in half and spread crabmeat mixture over 12 muffin halves. Freeze for 10 minutes. Cut each into 8 canapes. Refreeze until ready to serve (maximum 1 month). Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple well; add Jell-O.
Mix well; add cottage cheese.
Mix, then add Cool Whip.
This can be used as a salad or dessert.

title: sean's broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine until tender.
In a large bowl, combine thawed broccoli, rice, soup, water, cheese and milk. Add onions and celery (including margarine).
Mix and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind orange and cranberries together; add sugar.
Allow to stand an hour or more.
Mix Jell-O in hot water.
When thoroughly dissolved and cool enough to be syrupy, add orange and cranberry mixture and chopped walnuts.
May also add celery and crushed pineapple.
Pour into a casserole or mold and chill for several hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves and top with mayonnaise.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: toffee bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil, then line with Club crackers. Boil butter and brown sugar at least 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add nuts (optional).
Immediately pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes, then sprinkle with chocolate chips; when soft, spread evenly.

title: beef stroganoff 1
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Put a little mustard on meat and meat tenderizer also.
Let stay in refrigerator for a few hours.
Saute onion and mushrooms in garlic and butter.
Brown meat in drippings. Add soup and other ingredients.
Cook over low heat about 30 minutes until meat is tender.
Add sour cream last and garnish with parsley.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar, stir in vanilla.
Combine about 2 tablespoons flour with nuts, toss to coat well.
Add nuts and remaining flour to creamed mixture.
Roll small amount of dough into the shape of dates.
Place on baking sheet, bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and roll in powdered sugar. Makes three dozen.
(These keep well and are so-o-o good.)

title: old fashioned chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients quickly.
Pour into pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: weekend candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and creamer in a saucepan to soft ball stage.
Cool to lukewarm, about 30 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Stir until begins to thicken.
Add fruit and nuts.
Press into buttered pan.
Work quickly.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Combine raisins, water and soda and soak overnight.
Cream oil and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
With Pam, spray 5 clean vegetable cans. Fill cans halfway with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Sprinkle meat with oregano or salt and pepper.
Fry until light brown.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Cook cabbage and onion in butter until soft.
Season as desired.
Add cooked noodles and toss.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let margarine and cheeses soften.
Mix together with garlic salt.
Shape into ball.
Refrigerate to harden.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: apricot glow
directions: Sprinkle gelatin in cold water in 1-quart saucepan to soften. Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir in apricot nectar.

title: savory chili
directions: Heat olive oil in 5-quart Dutch oven.
Add garlic, onion, celery and parsley; saute until tender.
Add ground beef and brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain off drippings; reserve 3 tablespoons.
Add reserved drippings to meat mixture.
Stir in tomato paste, tomato sauce, water, chili powder, cayenne pepper, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
If desired, add red beans during last 15 minutes.
Let stand overnight and serve with cheese, onion or lettuce condiments.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mexican rice(original recipe)
directions: Mix rice, Ro-Tel tomatoes, garlic salt, onion salt and chili powder.
In separate bowl, mix sour cream and green chilies. Layer half of rice mixture in large casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Spread sour cream mixture over cheese.
Top with remaining rice mixture.
Heat in oven until hot and bubbly. Garnish with black olives or green onions or chopped tomatoes, if desired.

title: apple-nut coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Add to cream mixture alternately with sour cream.
Stir in apples.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: brownie cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Bring oleo, water and oil to boil.
Add to dry ingredients along with eggs, vanilla and milk.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased, well-floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: *Add boiled water after all other ingredients are mixed well.

title: lo-cal tamale pie
directions: Brown meat and onions; add tomato sauce, Mexicorn, carrots, chili powder and garlic.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix cornbread per instructions.
Put meat mixture in 12 x 7 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish.
Spoon cornbread over top of mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: eggnog pie
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Scald milk in top of double boiler.
In a bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Mix well. Add to scalded milk and cook until mixture is thick and smooth, about 15 minutes.
Stir a small amount of the mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Add egg yolk mixture to remaining mixture in boiler. Cook a few minutes longer.
Add butter and gelatin.
Stir.
Cool and then add vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream and pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle generously with nutmeg.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
This pie can be frozen.

title: a-1 chili
directions: For
thinner
chili use larger can tomato sauce and add 1/2 cup water.

title: lasagna
directions: Add mushrooms to sauce and use for spaghetti sauce.

title: linguini with chicken sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes; cover with hot water and soak until needed.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Cook onion in olive oil until lightly browned, then toss in chicken and garlic.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Remove chicken from skillet; add flour and broth.
Heat until bubbly.
Drain tomatoes and add them to sauce.
Add remaining ingredients.
Return chicken to pan.
Serve over linguini.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: In a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish, layer in thirds the noodles, ham and cheese.
Mix soup with sour cream, pepper, onion and peas.
Spread over top of layered ingredients; mix together. Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix together all ingredients and let set, covered, overnight in refrigerator.
Serve the next day.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add sugars.
Mix with oil and pumpkin, stirring until well combined with electric mixer (use slow speed).
Add eggs, one at a time, blending thoroughly.

title: top and bottom pie dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening until crumbly. Mix egg, water and vinegar.
Blend into flour mixture until moist. Don't overbeat.
Place dough ball in freezer 10 minutes to chill. Then roll out for pie.
Makes a 9-inch shell.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry garlic and bacon, add to mixture.
Bake in a slow oven (350°) for 1 hour.

title: easy caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut bread into 1-inch slices then down center.
Sprinkle chopped nuts in greased dish and lay bread in.
In a saucepan melt oleo and add brown sugar, vanilla, cinnamon and pudding mix.
Mix and pour over rolls.
Let rise until double and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: curried chicken breasts
directions: Place beans in bottom of casserole.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Spread mixture over beans.
Push in chicken breasts and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: redneck caviar
directions: Drain peas.
(Rinse if canned.)
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate, covered, overnight or longer.
Turn several times with slotted spoon to marinate.
If double or triple, reduce garlic and red pepper.
Remember that strong herbs have a "multiplier" effect.

title: jellied salad
directions: Drain the liquid from the pineapple and add water to make 1 cup.
Heat and add jello and lemon juice. Cool, then add whipped cream, carrots and pineapple.
Put the sugar and salt in the whipping cream. Pour into mold and cool until set.
Unmold by dipping in warm water for a few seconds.
Turn out onto plate and serve with any garnish you wish.

title: micro peanut brittle
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes; stir.
Microwave on High for 4 more minutes.
Stir in vanilla and butter.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Add baking soda and stir like crazy!
Pour onto a buttered sheet pan and spread.
Cool, then crack into pieces.

title: turkey pie
directions: Cook carrots and celery together in boiling salted water 15 minutes; drain, reserve liquid for gravy.
Blend flour, salt and fat; stir into hot liquid.
Cook and stir constantly until thickened.
Combine gravy, vegetables, and turkey.
Place in greased baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.
Remove from oven. Top with biscuits.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, oil and vanilla.
Add peanut butter and eggs. Sift dry ingredients together and add to peanut butter mixture. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 dozen.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onions in oil until soft.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 15 minutes.
This is great for chicken cooked on the grill, basting often with the sauce.

title: karlee's tuna salad
directions: Mix together, warm in the microwave (good cold, too).
Serve on a bed of lettuce with tomato.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, shortening and salt.
Whip egg, water and vinegar together; add to flour mixture.
Makes 2 crust 9 to 10-inch pie.
This is foolproof!!

title: finger licking mushroom smothered pork chops
directions: Rinse off pork chops with cider vinegar, then water; season to taste.
Cover with veggies and mushrooms; refrigerate overnight. In crock-pot, place meat, veggies and mushrooms.
Cover with mushroom sauce.
Cook on high for 4 to 6 hours, or on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with rice and your favorite veggies, or use as a dressing.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, the sour cream, pepper, pimentos and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook meat and onion together until meat is no longer pink. Add taco seasoning mix.
Add rest of ingredients; do not drain! Mix all together well and simmer for about 45 minutes.
Good served with grated Longhorn or Colby cheese on top and cornbread.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Shape ground beef in balls and place checker board fashion with potatoes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Slice onion and put rings around Tater Tots and ground beef.

title: nut kisses
directions: Beat whites until stiff.
Add flour and sugar, beating well. Add salt, vanilla and nuts slowly.
Drop by spoon onto baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Mix well by hand and form small rolls. Bake on greased sheet at 350° for 20 minutes or until delicately browned.
While hot, roll in cane sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: blueberry pudding
directions: Place blueberries in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and cinnamon.
Cream 3/4 cup sugar with butter.
Add milk.
Sift baking powder, salt and flour.
Add to butter mixture. Spread batter over blueberries.
Mix 1 cup sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over; do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or sauce.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Sift
together
flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Thoroughly cream the shortening, butter and brown sugar.
Add the eggs
and blend well.
Gradually add the flour mixture to the shortening and
mix
thoroughly.
Add
the
pecans and mix in well.
Drop onto a baking sheet by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart.
Bake at
for
to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: southold bread
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle yeast into warm (110°) water.
Add molasses and let stand 5 minutes, then stir to dissolve.
Add everything except the 3 flours and mix well.
By hand, stir in the rye and whole wheat flour, and most of the white flour until dough is stiff.
Shape into ball, brush lightly with oil.
Cover and let rise until doubled (punch down and let rise again if fine texture is desired).
Turn out on floured board, knead gently.
Shape into 2 large or 4 small loaves, put in pans and let rise until doubled. Bake at preheated 375° for 25 minutes, reduce heat to 350° and bake about 20 minutes more.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, oatmeal, salt and vanilla and mix.
In small cup, mix boiling water with baking soda, then add to dough and mix in.
Lastly, add nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake in oven preheated to 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 of stuffing mix in a dish.
Mix rest of ingredients except butter and crumbs.

title: fast-n-easy baked beans
directions: Mix all together and cook in microwave on High for 8 minutes. Stir halfway through.

title: strawberry sherbet
directions: Mix together.
Add milk to fill line.
Makes 1 gallon.
Stir and freeze.

title: soft and chewy brownies
directions: Melt chocolate squares over very low heat.
In a large bowl, mix butter, sugar, vanilla and chocolate.
Add eggs and mix well. Slowly add flour and mix until completely blended.
Grease pan and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: snappy rice
directions: Cook rice; add butter and onion to skillet and saute.
Mix all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and simmer until heated well.

title: tater muffins
directions: Mix flour and butter together until it looks like cornmeal. Beat egg, buttermilk and mashed potatoes together; add to flour and butter mixture.
Pour into a greased muffin pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 475°.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well. Form into loaves; pour tomato over each loaf. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Feeds 8 cowboys or 10 city slickers.

title: english trifle
directions: Spread jam between all ladyfingers.
Break into thirds into bottom of bowl.
Pour warm pudding over ladyfingers.
Top with whipped cream.

title: blender mousse
directions: In blender, combine morsels, sugar and eggs.
Add hot milk and liquor.
Blend at medium speed until mixture is smooth.
Pour in demitasse cups and chill in refrigerator 1 hour.
Garnish with whipped cream if desired.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: spinach dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend well.
Great on fresh spinach with bacon bits and hard-boiled eggs.

title: prehistoric pudding
directions: Crush cookies in food processor or zipper style plastic bag with rolling pin.
Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Stir in whipped topping and 1/2 of the crushed cookies.

title: bacony chicken breasts
directions: Cook chicken in frying pan until done.
May use oil or butter or a combination.
Place potatoes, mushrooms and bacon in a broiler pan under broiler in oven.
Cook 5 minutes, then turn and cook 5 minutes more or until bacon is done.
Serve potatoes, mushrooms and bacon over chicken.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine ingredients, except cheese.
Heat oil in heavy skillet. Pour in half of batter.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese over batter.
Pour in remaining batter and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: rolled sour cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat till smooth, add cream in which soda is dissolved. Mix. Add flour with baking powder and salt. Refrigerate
a few hours. Roll out dough, bake. Frost cookies when done.

title: freezer to table pot roast(yields 4 to 6 servings)
directions: In a shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole with tightly fitting lid, place frozen meat and cover tightly.
Microwave 40 minutes on 50% power.

title: chocolate turtle brownies
directions: Melt 1 cup morsels and butter in large, heavy saucepan over lowest possible heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs.
Add flour, sugar, vanilla and baking soda.
Stir well.
Spread batter into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining morsels and nuts.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Microwave caramels and milk in small, microwave-safe bowl on High power for 1 minute.
Stir, stirring until smooth.
Drizzle over warm brownies.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen brownies.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Spread rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sauce and broth with salt and pepper, thyme and marjoram.
Pour over rice. Arrange onion and peppers on top, then place browned pork chops on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: unbaked marshmallow squares
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, marshmallows, nuts and coconut in a large bowl.
Beat eggs in pan, add sugar and butter.
Place over a low heat and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Set aside to cool and add vanilla.
When cool, pour over and mix thoroughly with first mixture.
Press well into shallow pan.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cut in squares.

title: marshmallow chocolate cookies
directions: Melt the chocolate morsels, water and vanilla. Sift the flour, salt and soda.
Mix the shortening, brown sugar and egg.
Freeze the marshmallows.
Wrap in a tablespoon of cookie dough. Be sure to seal well. Bake 6 minutes in a 400° oven. Allow spreading room. Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: cheesy sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Saute mushrooms, green pepper and onion.
Mix all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan well.
Beat eggs; add sugar.
Pour in sour cream and oil.
Mix well.
Add poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.
Let cool. Sift powdered sugar over cake.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Separate chicken wings at joints.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour on chicken.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour (the longer, the better).
Turn chicken occasionally.

title: double deviled eggs
directions: Halve eggs. Remove yolks and in a small bowl, combine yolks, sour cream, deviled ham, mustard, pickle and pepper.
Fill whites.
Chill before serving.

title: hush puppies
directions: *Put in cup, then add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Beat egg before adding milk.

title: applesauce pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice well. Add applesauce. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crusts. Chill.

title: beef stew(slow cooker)
directions: Place meat in slow cooker. Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika. Stir into meat until coated. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Cover. Cook on low 10 to 12 hours or high 4 to 6 hours. Stir and serve.

title: cassata alla siciliana(sicilian cream cheese cake)
directions: *Cherries and pineapple are suggested, but any candied mixed fruit which includes cherries may be used.

title: rosemary cheese fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Place remaining ingredients in a bowl and mix in the butter.
Press mixture into a greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut into fingers. Serves 12.

title: date filled cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.

Add ingredients in order listed. Chill dough for several hours before rolling out. Roll fairly thin and cut with a biscuit cutter, allowing two for each cookie. (Or, you may place filling on one side of the circle of dough and fold over and crimp together with a fork, making a crescent shape.) Put a generous teaspoon of filling on one cookie and cover with another, pressing edges together.

title: spiral pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
In large bowl, combine olives, pepper, onion, parsley, pickle relish, cheese and dressing.
Add pasta and toss well.
Serves about 6.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Blend together first 7 ingredients.
Smooth out on platter. Then add layers of chili sauce, crab meat and parsley.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash and bake potatoes at 400° until done.
Let cool.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise, then scoop out pulp.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add 6 cups milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Add potato pulp, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons green onions, 1/2 of the bacon and 1 cup cheese.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Stir in sour cream.
Add extra milk, if necessary, for desired thickness.
Serve with remaining onion, bacon and cheese.

title: quick shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp, set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together in small pot the cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and cream of celery soup (optional).
Bring to a boil.
Boil fryer (do not salt).
Debone.
Spread half bag stuffing and margarine in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add chicken, then soup mixture, then 1 can of broth from boiled chicken.
Top with your other half stuffing mix.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top will be light brown.

title: pecan yummies
directions: Combine sugar, water and cinnamon; boil until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add a dash of salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pour over pecans and stir until cool.
Pour out on wax paper and break apart.

title: crunchy snack mix
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large roasting pan.
Combine margarine and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over cereal mixture, tossing gently.
Sprinkle with herb and spice blend.
Bake at 250° for 30 to 35 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Stir in raisins and cool.
Store in an airtight container. Yields 11 cups, 151 calories and 5 g fat from 1 cup serving.

title: oatmeal brownies
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ham loaf(serves 100)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ground meats, bread crumbs, onion, salt and mustard in a large container.
Add milk, tomato soup and eggs.
Mix well; divide into greased loaf pans and bake 1 hour.

title: old-time beef stew
directions: In Dutch oven, thoroughly brown meat in oil or butter, turning often.
Add 2 cups hot water and next 10 ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.
Remove bay leaves.
Add vegetables; cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: baked barbecue hamburger patties
directions: Dice the onions and place in a large bowl.
Add hamburger and mix thoroughly.
To this, add just enough Open Pit barbecue sauce to make mixture pasty.
Pinch out mixture into patties and place in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done in the center.

title: our perfect zesty chicken tortilla bake
directions: Mix dressing and flour in medium saucepan with wire whisk until well blended. Gradually add milk, stirring until well blended. Cook and stir on medium heat until sauce comes to a boil and thickens. Stir in half of the cheese. Reserve 1 c. of the prepared sauce.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.

title: peach pudding
directions: Cream butter and 2/3 cup sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk. Beat until smooth.
Pour over peaches that have been covered with 1 cup sugar in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage and taters
directions: Cut sausage into bite size pieces and cut potatoes in small, thin pieces.
Chop onion and cook over medium heat.
Add sausage and potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 30 minutes to an hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let sit in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.
Use for dip with fresh fruits, or pour over fresh fruit in a parfait dish for dessert.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix the flour with the milk until it dissolves.
Saute the onions in a frying pan; add the milk mixture, stirring constantly, until it thickens.
Blend in the cheese.
When the cheese melts, add the broccoli.
Coat a casserole dish with vegetable spray and pour the mixture into it; add the egg whites and mix gently.
Cut the phyllo dough in half.
Top the casserole mixture with layers of phyllo dough sprayed with the vegetable spray.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves eight.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Blend eggs, salad oil, walnuts and prunes.
Add to flour and beat until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jambayala in microwave
directions: In a 3-quart dish add oil and onion.
Cook 4 minutes in microwave.
Add shallots and everything else except meat and rice. Cook for 3 minutes in microwave until water boils.
Add rice and meat and cook covered in microwave at 50% power for 12 minutes. Stir.
Put back in microwave at 50% power for 12 minutes.
Let stand for 8 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: rosy pickled eggs
directions: Combine juice, vinegar, bay leaf and pickling spices in large pot; mix in water and salt mixture.
Mix well.
Remove shells from hard-boiled eggs; add eggs to juice mixture together with onion rings.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 to 4 days.

title: dick howell slaw
directions: Boil 20 minutes; put in jars.

title: chicken florentine in phyllo
directions: Drain spinach; press between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Set aside.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoon butter in a medium skillet until tender.
Combine onion, spinach, Ricotta and next 6 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well.
Place 2 sheets of phyllo on a flat surface (keep remaining phyllo covered); brush with butter.
Place 1 chicken breast half in center of phyllo, 3-inches from bottom.
Spoon about 1/3 cup spinach mixture over chicken.
Fold bottom of phyllo over spinach mixture.
Fold sides of phyllo over chicken, wrapping like a package.
Roll jellyroll fashion.
Place seam side down in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Repeat with remaining phyllo, butter, chicken and spinach mixture. Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 8.

title: brown sugar nut bar
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar (packed).
Mix in flour. Press in the bottom of a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: apple brownie
directions: Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add onion, milk and egg; stir.
Shape into small patties about the size of a hulled walnut, spanking them a little as you shape to get rid of air pockets.
Drop into hot fish grease to brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: walnut dressing
directions: Soften cream cheese; add walnuts and all other ingredients. Beat with blender or rotary beater.
Store in refrigerator.

title: zahtar
directions: Combine zahtar with sesame seed and sufficient oil to form a thin paste.
Mix well.
Make patties of basic dough and flatten to form circles with a 7-inch diameter.
Spread zahtar mixture on top, pressing it in with fingers.
Place patties on oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 470° for about 10 minutes.
Cut circles into wedges (like pizza) and serve.
May be eaten warm or cold.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix sugar and baking soda into egg whites.
Add finely crushed Ritz crackers and chopped pecans. Mix well and add vanilla.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Cook at 300° for 45 minutes (light golden brown).
Let cool and top with whipped cream.
Store in fridge.

title: light fruit pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O completely in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir until Jell-O is thickened. Remove any unmelted ice.
Blend in Cool Whip, then whip until smooth.
Fold in peaches.
Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Chill 2 hours.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables. Bring vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper to a boil.
Pour over canned vegetables and add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and marinate overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat the egg yolks and whole egg until well mixed.
Beat in cold water and salt.
Stir the flour in with a spoon.
The dough will be stiff, and you may have to knead in last of flour.
Divide dough in 3 parts.
Roll very thin, then cover with cloth until partially dry.
Roll up as for jelly roll, then slice with sharp knife.
Shake out strips; allow to dry before using.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Cut dates in half or smaller.
Pour boiling water over dates. Let stand while you cream shortening.
Add sugar and egg.
Beat well.
Drain water from dates.
Add flour, soda and salt; sifted together.
Beat well.
Add dates, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in loaf pan at 350°.
Makes 2 small loaf pans or 1 long loaf pan.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and the 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix with margarine. Press into a 12 x 20 x 2 1/2-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: fancy fish made easy
directions: Mix egg, butter, lemon juice and lemon pepper in bowl.
Using your fish of choice, dip into mixture, coating fish well and line bottom of shallow baking dish.
Pour remaining mixture on top of fish.
Cover fish with crumbled Ritz crackers and additional lemon pepper to taste.
Bake at 325° for approximately 25 minutes until fish is flaky.

title: sweet potato souffle for sunday dinner
directions: Mix together; pour into buttered pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Just before souffle is done, cover top with miniature marshmallows.
If you like raisins, you can add raisins to mixture before cooking.

title: hot wings
directions: Deep fry until crispy.
Add all ingredients to saucepan and bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Add wings until coated.
Remove from pan after coated.

title: homestyle macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Drain
well and cool.
Add other ingredients.
(Use garlic salt and celery seed for variety.)
Let stand 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Add 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Mix well.
It's ready to serve.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine
corn meal, salt and soda; blend well.	Stir in shortening; add sour cream, corn and eggs, mixing well.
Spoon half
of
batter into a greased heated 8 or 9-inch heavy skillet. Sprinkle
with cheese and chilies.	Cover with remaining corn bread
mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: green rice
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 12.

title: mam's refrigerator rolls
directions: Heat milk, sugar and oleo until oleo and sugar are dissolved. Sift together 3 c. flour, salt, baking powder, and soda.
Add dry yeast.
Add to warm milk mixture.
Beat all together well.
Then add rest of flour and mix well.
Refrigerate dough overnight in well greased bowl.
Roll out dough while you divide in half.
Brush with melted oleo.
Cut in size desired.
Fold over half.
Let rise until double, about 2 hrs. after placed in pan.
Bake at 450 degrees for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: old-fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry for 9-inch one crust.
Beat eggs slightly with a rotary beater; beat in remaining ingredients. Pour into pie crust and bake 15 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut green peppers in half crosswise.
Salt the insides. Combine ground beef, rice, egg, catsup, onion, salt and pepper. Fill peppers with meat mixture.
Place in a Dutch oven and cover with tomatoes.
Cover and cook 1 hour.

title: chili manicotti
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and garlic in hot oil until tender. Stir in condensed soup and the water; heat through.
Cook manicotti in boiling, salted water for 8 to 10 minutes; drain. Combine eggs, cottage cheese, 1 cup American cheese and peppers; mix well.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of the cheese mixture into each manicotti shell.
Pour half the soup mixture into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with manicotti.
Pour remaining soup over all, being sure manicotti are coated.
Cover; bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 2 or 3 minutes more.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chili reno's
directions: Arrange chilies to cover a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with cheese.
In a bowl, beat eggs, then beat in milk.
Add Bisquick mix gradually.
Beat until smooth; pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done in center.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Combine sugars and syrup. Bring ingredients to boil.
Then remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, peanuts and corn flakes. Press into cake pan.
Cover with chocolate.
Melt in oven and spread over the top.

title: christmas nuggets
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients; add sugar.
Add shortening and mix in with fork.
Add unbeaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Add fruit, nuts and milk.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: carrot cake ring
directions: About 4 hours before serving or day ahead:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan.

title: mom's best potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until tender.
Skin and grate.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to potatoes.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until hot.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Combine sugar, oleo, eggs and lemon juice; mix well.
Add coconut, pecans and raisins.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: In deep mixing bowl on low speed, beat the cherry pie filling for a couple of seconds. Add the dry cake mix; continue beating until both ingredients are thoroughly mixed. Spray baking pan with Pam. Spread cake mixture evenly into pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in middle of cake comes out clean.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Sift flour onto a large board.
Make a well in center.
Add salt, eggs and water.
Knead dough thoroughly about 1 minute, until it is stiff and smooth.

Add more flour if dough is too thin. Cover and set aside 10 minutes while filling is being prepared. Then divide dough into 3 parts and roll each part out on a lightly floured board to paper thinness.
Cut into 2-inch circles with cookie cutter or the top of a glass.
Cut 2 rounds for each ravioli.
Place a heaping teaspoon of desired filling in the center of 1 circle and cover with another circle.
Press edges together with a fork to seal.
Cook in 8 quarts of boiling water until dough is tender.
Serve with any tomato or meat sauce and sprinkle with fresh grated cheese.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and all ingredients, except nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Chop nuts and sprinkle in pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: wet burrito
directions: Cook meat and drain.
Add seasoning and water. Put meat into large flour shells and roll.
Put in greased 1-by-inch layer pan. Put 1/2 of cheese on top of burrito and pour enchilada sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, onions, black or green olives and other half of cheese.

title: hearty stuffed peppers
directions: Prepare potatoes as directed, except reduce water to 1 1/4 cups; cool slightly.
Stir in egg.
Brown ground beef and onion; pour off excess fat.
Stir beef into potatoes.
Cut tops from peppers and remove seeds: simmer in small amount of water for 5 minutes; drain. Spoon potato filling into peppers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with tomato sauce.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: mini pizza
directions: Put sauce and cheese on muffin.
Place in toaster oven until cheese melts and brown.
Sprinkle on oregano before eating.

title: special corn bread
directions: Mix baking mix, cornmeal and sugar in bowl.
Add eggs and milk; beat until blended.
Pour into hot skillet with 1/4 stick of butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Tastes a lot like Maire Callenders.

title: baked alaska
directions: Cut cake in half lengthwise.
Place slice on board. Slice ice cream and place on cake. Cover with slice of cake.
Cover completely with stiffly beaten egg whites to which sugar and vanilla have been added.
Bake in
a 450° oven about 4 to 5 minutes. Serve at once.

title: chicken nachos
directions: Mix soup, salsa and chicken.
Heat slowly.
Serve over chips. Top with onions and olives.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend flour, butter and confectioners sugar thoroughly.
Press evenly in square 8 x 8-inch pan, building up 1/2-inch sides.
Bake 20 minutes. Beat the rest of the ingredients together.
Pour over crust and bake about 25 minutes more.
Cool well. Cut into squares.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Brown onion, celery and green pepper in butter until tender. Add all other ingredients, including spaghetti, and mix well (except cheese).
Put into greased casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until cheese has melted and is bubbling.

title: quiche
directions: Mix cream and eggs.
Add flour, salt and pepper in bowl.
Whip good.
Add butter.
Put cheese and crumbled bacon in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Slowly pour egg mixture over cheese and bacon. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: taco supper casserole
directions: Coat 2-quart (9 x 13) baking dish with cooking spray or Crisco.
Add potatoes and some onion.
Dissolve bouillon in hot water and pour 1/2 cup over potatoes.
Combine meat, taco seasoning, milk, 1/4 cup salsa, oats, egg and remaining onion. Mix well and pour over potatoes.
Combine remaining 1 cup salsa and broth.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until crisp-tender and drain.
Add onion and green pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients in a saucepan and heat just enough to dissolve sugar and mix well. Pour over carrot mixture and refrigerate.
Keeps several days and gets better with age.

title: clam pie
directions: Mix together the ingredients in bowl.
Using vegetable cooking oil spray a pie plate.
Pour clam mixture into the pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes two generous servings.

title: cherry drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and combine all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased baking sheet.
Top with cherry halves and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Mix Bisquick, salt, poultry seasoning and paprika together. Dip chicken in milk, then in seasoning mixture.
Drizzle melted butter over chicken.
Bake at 375° uncovered for 45 minutes.
This mixture will cover 8 chicken breasts.

title: egg gravy
directions: Fry salt pork.
Remove, then add flour.
Stir until browned. Add water, stirring constantly until thick.
Put eggs in, then add water.

title: glorified rice
directions: Combine all ingredients, except whipped cream and strawberries.
Mix well; chill.
Fold in whipped cream and strawberries if desired.
Chill again.
Serve.

title: chicks in easter basket cake
directions: Empty all boxes in a mixing bowl.
Add Parkay (or butter), cream cheese and water.
Blend on medium speed of mixer until fluffy.
Blend well for about a minute.
Set aside.

title: perfectly easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together and drop from a teaspoon onto a foil-lined cookie sheet.
Depress slightly.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 1 to 2 dozen cookies.

title: "monster" bread appetizer
directions: Slice French bread lengthwise.
Spread margarine evenly over two sides.
Place in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Meanwhile mix mayonnaise and Parmesan in bowl.
Remove bread from oven and spread mixture over two halves.
Place under broiler until bubbly and golden brown.
Cut into thin triangles and serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water and cook until soft. Mash and add remaining ingredients. If it's too thick, add milk.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: baked swiss chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and wine; spoon over cheese slices placed on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix and drizzle with butter.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar gradually.
Add pumpkin, water and oil and beat thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients; mix until blended. Bake in 3 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake at 350°.
Mix mashed pumpkin and remainder of ingredients together.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust and bake until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place
cooked
broccoli
in
greased baking dish. Blend soup, milk
and
cheese, heating until cheese is melted.	Pour over broccoli.
Top
with
crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Dissolve gelatin in water.
Set aside. Empty contents of cake mix into large mixing bowl.
Add oil and flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add gelatin mixture and continue beating batter until it is well mixed.
Use a 9-inch tube pan.
Put two layers of waxed paper in bottom.
Grease the tube and sides of pan and dust lightly with flour.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately with spatula and glaze with the following, which you have mixed while cake is baking.
This is a very moist cake and freezes well.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix bread crumbs, 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese and 1 tablespoon butter.
Combine onions, peppers, stock and 1 tablespoon butter in pan.
Cover and cook over medium heat until limp.
Add mushrooms and garlic; cook, uncovered, until all the liquid has evaporated.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions and sliced mushrooms in butter; drain.
Add all other ingredients (except soup and sour cream).
Brown 5 minutes. Then add soup.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: posh squash
directions: Cook squash until tender. Drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until heated thoroughly.

title: homemade salad dressing
directions: Mix together sugar, salt and mustard.
Add beaten eggs and mix well. Add vinegar, water and milk. Cook in double boiler until thick and creamy.
Makes 2 cups.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Let stand several hours to blend flavors.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with Doritos.
Place chicken on top of Doritos.
Mix soups, broth, Ro-Tel and onion together. Alternate soup mixture, cheese and Doritos.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: scalloped corn and oysters
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and the 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with the remaining cracker crumbs which have been mixed with the butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted halfway to center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, soda, salt, and cocoa.
Mix well, add water and stir until smooth.
Add vanilla and mayonnaise.
Bake at 350 degrees until lightly brown and separating from sides a little.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown the ground chuck and onion; drain well. Add the spaghetti sauce or tomato sauce. Add the Italian seasoning, garlic salt and oregano to taste. Simmer all ingredients 1 hour or more.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Cut veal in 2-inch cubes.
Dredge with seasoned flour, minced onion and garlic.
Cook veal, onion and garlic in fat until browned; add remaining ingredients.
Turn into casserole, cover and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: fried chicken
directions: Increase amounts of flour, etc. if cooking large quatities of chicken.

title: flank steak fix-up
directions: Rub steak with garlic; sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt and the pepper.
Cut meat crosswise into 4 to 6 serving pieces.
In large skillet, cook bacon.
Drain bacon; reserve 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Place slice of bacon on each piece of meat; roll up and secure with wooden picks.
Coat rolls with flour.
Brown rolls in the reserved bacon drippings over medium heat.
Stir together remaining ingredients; pour over meat.
Cover tightly; simmer 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Place rolls on warm platter; remove wooden picks.
Heat sauce to boiling, stirring constantly.
Pour over rolls.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: rice mushroom casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Put in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover with rice evenly and then pour soups over rice. Dump mushrooms in middle.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, Crisco oil and eggs.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients 2 to 3 times.
Add to egg mixture and beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Add grated carrots; beat 1 minute. Spread in a greased and floured pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting (recipe follows).

title: black bean salad
directions: In large bowl combine red and yellow pepper, chopped tomatoes, green onion, black beans and white beans.
Stir gently to combine. Set aside.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Blend sour cream and cream cheese with mixer until smooth. Add other ingredients, mixing well with large spoon.
Chill thoroughly.

title: easter egg leftovers
directions: Slice rolls in half.
Fill as desired with mix.
Wrap each roll individually in foil.
These freeze well.
Heat if desired: fresh, 350° for 1/2 hour; frozen, 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: hot macadamia dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cream cheese and milk.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in chipped beef, onion, green pepper, garlic, pepper and ginger.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into baking dish. Saute nuts in butter until thoroughly glazed.
Sprinkle nuts over beef mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through. Serve hot with crackers.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Put everything in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix with fork. Mix well.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first six ingredients.	Spoon into prepared pie crust.
Cover with top crust.
Seal top crust by pressing with fork all the way around edge of crust.
Slit top crust and brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine milk, cream cheese and lemon juice until smooth with blender.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Pour 1 can of cherry pie filling on top.

title: mama's butter brickle cake
directions: Sift together in large bowl the first 4 ingredients.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat vigorously by hand or with electric mixer.
Add 3 large egg whites.
Beat 2 minutes longer. Pour into 2 (8 or 9-inch) greased and floured round pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and ice with Browned Butter Icing.

title: company potatoes
directions: Saute margarine and onions in skillet.
Add to hash browns (frozen).
Mix with soup and sour cream and spread in a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish.
Mix cheese and corn flakes and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in frying pan until done.
Drain off liquid and put in a baking dish or pan.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Stir and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until the cheese melts, usually about 15 minutes.
If you want to you can make ahead of time and while the cheese is melting it will get warm.

title: sho fly cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and butter, work into fine crumbs. Keep out 1 1/2
cups
for
topping.
Mix
water,
molasses and soda. Add remaining crumbs and mix well until batter is thin. Pour in pan that
is
greased and floured.
Sprinkle the 1 1/2 cups of crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jello dessert
directions: Break angel food cake off in bite size pieces.
Drop in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Make sure bottom is covered.
In a bowl, mix jello with hot water.
When dissolved, add cold water.
Stir in strawberries, then pour over angel food cake evenly.
Make sure cake is covered.
Put into refrigerator until set (may set overnight).
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla and pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: lorene's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add onion and cook until it is transparent.
Add Italian seasoning, chili powder and minced garlic.
Stir into hamburger and onion mixture.
Then add tomato sauce.
Stir.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix with mixer and chill.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet with onion, 1 teaspoon oregano, salt and pepper; stir in catsup, pizza sauce, soups, brown sugar and mushrooms.
Simmer until blended.
Place noodles in greased casserole; stir in beef mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and remaining oregano.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: almond poppy seed pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 2 loaf pans. Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl and beat
at medium speed until well mixed (2 to 3 minutes), scraping bowl often. Pour into prepared loaf pans and bake for 45 minutes.
Glaze if desired.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: To make sauce, cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more. Remove from heat.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Place flour, salt and baking powder in mixing bowl.
Add shortening and mix well.
Add lukewarm water and blend well.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead at least 50 strokes.
Divide into 12 equal sized pieces and form into balls.
Cover with a cloth and let stand 15 minutes.
Roll each ball into a round tortilla, about 8 inches in diameter.
Cook on moderately hot iron grill, ungreased, turning once.

title: bean casserole
directions: Fry all the sausage; mix all ingredients. Top with bacon slices. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Combine meat, onion, rice, milk and seasoning.
Mix well.
Cut ends off zucchini.
With apple corer, scoop out centers, reserving them for sauce.
Fill zucchini loosely with meat mixture.
Heat tomato sauce in skillet.
Lay stuffed zucchini in sauce and add zucchini centers and any left over meat mixture.
Simmer uncovered 1 hour or until rice is tender, stirring sauce occasionally. Serve with sauce.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water.
Fold in pineapple, apple, nuts and cranberry sauce.
Pour into mold. Chill until firm.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise; place in center of mold.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Remove and add 1 cup grated cheese (if you like cheese) to top and bake at 350° for another 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ritzy chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg whites until nearly stiff.
Slowly add sugar, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Continue beating until stiff.
Fold in Ritz cracker crumbs and pecans.
Pour in greased and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and top with Cool Whip with Nestle Quik (about 3 or 4 tablespoons) mixed in Cool Whip. May also use ice cream, if desired.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth and drain; reserve about a cup of broth.
Mix all ingredients well and bake in covered casserole dish at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice eggplant 1/2-inch thick, leaving skin on. Arrange slices in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Layer onion, green peppers and tomato slices.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and flour on top. Dot with butter and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Top with Mozzarella. Cover top lightly with foil and bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until eggplant is done.

title: french toast
directions: Take a couple of eggs and crack them.
Then scramble them up with some milk.
Put bread in eggs until covered.
Put on griddle until cooked.
Cut up and pour on syrup, then eat.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Mix pudding, cream cheese and milk together.
Cool in refrigerator until thick and easy to spread.
Spoon pudding mixture over cake.
Sprinkle crushed pineapple over pudding.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple. Sprinkle on coconut and nuts.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery and almonds with mayonnaise. Add onion, salt, monosodium glutamate and lemon juice that have been mixed together. Put in a 2-quart casserole. Top with potato chips and Cheddar cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 400°. Serves 6.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to package directions and set aside.
Saute onions and celery in butter.
Simmer until blended. Fold in rice and broccoli.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: mushroom scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix soup, cheese, pimiento, salt and mushroom stems and pieces.
Gradually stir in cream and potatoes.
Pour into a shallow baking dish.
Top with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix together meat and bread crumbs.
Add milk, soup mix, onion and salt.
Beat eggs, then add to meat mixture.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Cook onion in margarine until nearly done.
Add can of tomatoes with green chilies and heat.
In top of double boiler, melt Velveeta and add tomato mixture.
Heat together.
Can be served from double boiler or from chafing dish.
Must be kept hot. Dip with large Fritos.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion; drain.
Stir in seasonings and tomato sauce; simmer 20 minutes.
Prepare noodles and drain.
Put meat mixture in bottom of pan first, then noodles, then cheese; repeat.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge frosting
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine the sugar and heavy cream.
Place over moderate heat and, stirring constantly, bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate, butter and vanilla, continuing to stir until chocolate and butter melt.
Turn into a bowl and cool to room temperature, stirring occasionally.
Refrigerate, stirring frequently until thickened and of a good spreading consistency. Use to frost a cake before the frosting sets completely.

title: pineapple custard pie
directions: Cream softened butter or margarine with sugar.
Add flour. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Drain juice from pineapple and add pineapple and cream to mixture.
Mix well. Pour into 2 (9-inch) unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: ginger chicken with pea pods
directions: Marinate chicken breast halves, garlic, ginger, sesame oil and soy sauce for several hours in refrigerator.

title: frittata
directions: You will also need nonstick cooking spray.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Rinse and put in heavy large saucepan. Add other ingredients except Cool Whip and nutmeg.
Cook until it starts to bubble (stir constantly and do not let it boil hard) on high heat.
Cook 1 minute after it starts to bubble.
Remove from heat.
Cover in refrigerator with nutmeg sprinkled on top.
Serve with spoonful of Cool Whip on top.
This will thicken as it cools in refrigerator.

title: fiesta salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours. Garnish with cilantro and serve with tortilla chips.
Yields approximately 3 1/2 cups.

title: fantastic fruit salad
directions: Heat on low, eggs, lemon juice, sugar, margarine and marshmallows until melted.
Stir well and cool.
Add whipping cream (unwhipped), almonds, bananas, pineapple, oranges and fruit cocktail.
Mix well and let sit at least 12 hours.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Cut Crisco in flour.
Add milk.
Work to make soft dough. Knead dough gently on floured surface.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness cut and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 475° or until golden brown.
Brush with cooking oil while hot.

title: penuche
directions: Combine sugar, cream and butter.
Boil to soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts, fruit and coconut.
Beat until mixture holds its shape.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut into squares.

title: western gingerbread
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients and reserve 1/2 cup crumb mixture.
Add the egg, sorghum, sour milk and soda.
Mix and beat well.
Pour into prepared pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Cut 1 tablespoon of butter into reserved crumb mix and sprinkle over top of batter.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together; form ball.
Roll and cut like biscuits.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: In a bowl put thinly sliced rhubarb.
Cover with cold water for 1 minute.
Drain.
In another bowl, mix flour, egg yolks, sugar and butter.
Beat well.
Add rhubarb and put in 1 unbaked pie shell.
Bake until done.
Then cover with meringue.
Return to oven and bake until brown.
Bake pie 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fondue(tomato cheese)
directions: Heat juices in a pan until bubbly; add cheese a little at a time.
Remove to fondue pot.
Use French bread for dipping.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and add enough mayonnaise to form into ball. Roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, butter, water and vinegar. Cook over hot water until smooth and thick; season to taste. Add beets. Heat thoroughly.

title: cranberry glazed duck
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper over duck.
Heat butter and sauce. Place on broiler rack.
Brush with butter mixture every 5 minutes. Broil about 30 minutes.
Pour remaining glaze over duck when done.

title: chicken stock
directions: Simmer all together for 2 hours, uncovered.
Remove bones, veggies, peppercorns, etc.; strain.
Let cool thoroughly in refrigerator; remove fat.
This freezes well.

title: far east casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in a casserole.
Mix together.
Top with bread crumbs and sliced almonds.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken stuffing balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, blend together egg, butter and water.
Stir in stuffing crumbs, sauce mix packet and cheese until well blended.
Press and shape into 1-inch balls. Place on greased baking sheet and bake 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes approximately 3 dozen balls.
May be baked ahead, then refrigerated or frozen.
Reheat to serve.

title: caramel icing
directions: Brown first 2 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
While this is browning, heat 2 cups sugar and 1 cup milk together.
Add to browned sugar and butter.
Cook about 3 minutes to the soft ball stage.
Cool slightly, then beat to spreading consistency.

title: sherry wine cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth, about 3 minutes.
Pour batter into tube pan that is well-greased and floured.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if so desired.

title: tofu yogurt
directions: Cut the tofu into 1/4-inch cubes.
In a bowl, combine the yogurt and tofu.
This is one of the few ways to make the strange consistency of firm or extra firm tofu palatable.

title: one-bowl chocolate cake
directions: Put flour, sugar, baking soda, cocoa and salt in bowl and blend.
Add oil and buttermilk.
Beat slowly and add 2 eggs.
Beat well and add boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan (cupcakes 12 minutes).
Batter will be very thin.

title: alma's squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix in stuffing.
Line a long casserole dish with stuffing, saving a little for topping.
In a mixing bowl mix rest of ingredients.
Pour into casserole over stuffing. Sprinkle rest of stuffing on top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes. Makes 1 large or 2 small casseroles.

title: cocoalight cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add shortening and 3/4 cup milk.
Beat vigorously.
Add 1/2 cup milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly for 2 minutes. Pour into 3 cake pans (greased and floured).
Bake 25 or 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: nacho supreme
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Add refried beans and water. Mix and let simmer on low heat for 15 minutes.
Place the tortilla chips in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle the meat and bean mixture over the chips.
Cover with cheese. Sprinkle tomato, pepper and onion over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until the cheese is melted.
Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: granola snack
directions: Mix together quick oats, wheat germ, coconut, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Add the honey and mix with fingers.
Add oil and vanilla and mix.
Spread on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: daniel j's penne pasta with chicken(yield: 8 servings.)
directions: Toss chicken with marinade in a non-aluminum bowl.
