Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour or up to 1 day.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream margarine, add sugar; beat.
Add egg; beat.
Add nuts, flour and vanilla; mix well.
Spread 2/3 of batter in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread about 1/4 inch of any filling over batter, then spoon remaining batter randomly over filling.
Bake for 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Cut in squares and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: pam vernon's original milky way cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients together except Milky Ways.
If cookie dough is too sticky, add a little more flour.
Wrap just enough cookie dough around each candy to cover completely.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven until they look almost done (approximately 8 minutes).
Leave on cookie sheet until set.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: pork tenderloin delight
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and sherry.
Pour over meat.
Saute mushrooms and put on top of sauce.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: homemade baklava(international)
directions: Sieve the flour and salt; put the butter over and knead very well. Put water over the mixture 1 tablespoon after the other and knead until you have a playable dough. Leave the dough to rest for half an hour. Make 12 equal pieces of the dough. Roll each piece to 13 x 9-inch. Grease 13 x 9-inch glass pan with butter. Put 6 rolling pieces over the other, spreading butter between each piece before putting the other piece over. Spread the top of the sixth piece with butter, then spread the filling over and put the other 6 pieces, repeating the same procedure. Spread the top with butter; cut the baklava into triangles, then bake in 300° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until the top becomes red in colour. Take the Baklava out, spread with generous amount of sugar syrup and serve.

title: almond crescents
directions: In a shallow pan toast almonds lightly.
In a bowl, cream butter until light and fluffy; add the 2 tablespoons powdered sugar and egg yolk, mixing well, stir in almonds.
In another bowl, combine flour and baking powder; gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture, blend until smooth.
Pinch off walnut size pieces of dough and shape into crescents.
Place on ungreased baking sheets, about 1 inch apart.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Let cool for 5 minutes.
Sift 1 1/2 to 2 cups powdered sugar over top to cover cookies.
Let stand until cool.
Store in a tightly covered container.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: peanut bread
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually and beat until creamy.
Add other ingredients, except peanuts, to creamed mixture and mix well.
Add peanuts and mix again.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: corn flakes cookies
directions: Combine softened margarine, Crisco oil, white sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add plain flour, salt and soda.
Then add corn flakes, Quaker oats and pecans.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet which has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
(Note:
Refrain from cooking too long.)
Yields 8 to 10 dozen.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Blend eggs, flour and sugar with mixer.
Add pineapple.
Mix well with wooden spoon.
Pour into casserole dish.
(If your casserole dish is large enough, you can mix everything in it instead of in a separate bowl.)
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: banana pudding pie
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar and butter together and press in bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Put in refrigerator to chill for 30 minutes.

title: depression cake
directions: In a large saucepan, put raisins and 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil, turn down heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add shortening, let melt.
Add 1/2 cup cold water, sugar, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, salt and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add flour; mix well.
Put in lightly greased and floured square pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes until done.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice according to package directions using 3 cups of broth in place of water.
Fluff with fork and set aside.
Parboil broccoli; drain thoroughly.
In 12-inch skillet, melt 1/2 cup of butter.
Saute onion and mushrooms until soft.
Blend in flour and cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add remaining 3 cups of broth and cream, still stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture just comes to a boil; add salt and pepper to taste.
Place cooked rice in a buttered 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Spread drained broccoli on top of rice and cover with sauce.
In small skillet, melt 2 tablespoons of butter; add bread crumbs and cook, stirring, until lightly browned. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, until sauce bubbles, about 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
Good with a boned chicken breast and simple green salad.

title: steve's bachelor soup
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain.
Add soup, beans, mushrooms and 1/2 package of spaghetti (broken up) into large pan.
Add picante sauce to taste, depending on how well you like picante sauce.

title: crab meat mold
directions: Heat mushroom soup (don't add water).
Add gelatin.
Cool. Soften cream cheese.
Add to soup mixture.
Add onion, celery, mayonnaise and crab meat.
Pour into mold.
Let set overnight. Serve on crackers.

title: italian cream cake short version(easy)
directions: In large bowl, mix ingredients. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan. Bake at 350° approximately 35 minutes or until cake is done.

title: persimmon drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and persimmon pulp and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Add vanilla and orange extract, nuts and raisins to first mixture and mix well.
Add dry ingredients last.
It will make a stiff dough.
Drop onto greased tin.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in cream cheese until it is in little bits.
Chill until it is only partly congealed. Fold in pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.

title: california carol's cold spaghetti salad
directions: Marinate green pepper, red onion and celery in salad seasoning and salad dressing overnight.
Cook spaghetti in salted water with oil; rinse in cold water.
Toss with marinade.
Garnish with avocado, artichoke hearts and olives.

title: whole-wheat muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add beaten eggs, milk, oil and sugar.
Stir just until moist.
Bake in greased muffin pans for 15 minutes at 425°.

title: caramel apple delight
directions: Blend first four ingredients using electric mixer.
Mix in sour cream by hand.
Use as a dip for apple slices.

title: foiled corn on the cob
directions: Husk corn right before cooking.
Place each ear on a piece of aluminum foil.
Brush corn with herb spread; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake 450° for 25 minutes, turning several times.

title: coconut lemon sours
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in small bowl.
Cut in butter until like coarse meal.
Press into ungreased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: beef and bean barbecue
directions: Cook beef and vegetables in hot fat until soft.
Add tomato sauce, water, garlic, vinegar, mustard, thyme, brown sugar and seasonings.
Blend well; simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour beans into casserole.
Pour meat mixture over beans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix all together and then chill dough. Roll into quarter size balls and bake at 375° about 12 to 15 minutes. When cooled, roll in powdered sugar.

title: old-fashioned brownies
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Stir in sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add shortening and chocolate, followed by flour and walnuts.
Mixture will be coarse in texture.
Spread in a greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pepper chicken
directions: Remove skin and fat from chicken.
Place chicken in large skillet.
Mix soy sauce, 1 tablespoon water and garlic powder. Pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour, turning chicken once.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes. Scatter water chestnuts and green pepper slices on chicken.
Cover and simmer until chicken is tender, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: almost a meal casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine browned and drained beef, onion, tomatoes with liquid, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Spoon into greased 3-quart casserole.
Layer the potatoes, flour, corn, lima beans and green peppers on top; cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with the cheese and continue baking, uncovered, for 30 minutes longer.
Very good for preparing ahead of time.
To reheat, place foil loosely over top and reheat in oven for 20 minutes.

title: terry's famous cornish pastry
directions: Roll out pastry, trim fat off beef and cut into paper thin slices. Mix meat and vegetables.
Put mixture into pastry and season well.
Top with butter. Dampen pastry edges with water and draw up edges to meet at top of pastry.
Pinch together and poke top with fork to vent.
Brush pastry with beaten egg.
Place on greased baking tray.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake 30 minutes more.
Can serve with gravy or A.1. steak sauce on the side.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar with flour.
Beat egg yolks with milk.
Add sugar mixture to milk mixture.
Cook in heavy pan until thick; add butter and vanilla.
Beat, then add coconut.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until holds peak.
Add 8 teaspoons sugar. Beat until very stiff.
Top pie with egg whites and let brown in a slow oven.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Add green pepper, onion, salt and pepper; use some garlic salt.
When brown, add tomato paste, tomato soup, water, oregano, basil and parsley flakes.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Makes enough sauce to go with 1 1/2 pounds cooked spaghetti.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: ham and cheese pockets
directions: Take 4-inch squares of pastry and spread lightly with mustard. Top half of each square with strip of cheese and ham.
Fold pastry in half and press edges together and seal with fork.
Place pastries about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Brush lightly with egg.
Pierce top of each pastry with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cherries 'n' spice cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Drain cherries, reserving 1 cup liquid. Place cherries in a 2-quart round baking dish; set aside.
In a small bowl, mix sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in 1 cup cherry liquid until smooth.
Pour over cherries, stir.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbling vigorously around edges. Place rolls, cinnamon-side up, in a single layer over hot cherry mixture.
Reduce heat to 400° and bake 15 minutes longer or until rolls are golden brown.
Spread rolls with icing and sprinkle with lemon rind.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: country casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box; set aside. In a large skillet, put a little oil.
Slice up the sausage; cut the red pepper into strips.
Add the oregano; cook on medium heat. Add the broccoli and cover.
Stir occasionally until tender.
Mix with macaroni and cheese.
Serve.
Serves 6.

title: saturday chicken
directions: Sprinkle salt and garlic salt on chicken. Sprinkle paprika liberally over chicken. Arrange chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the soup and whipping cream in a bowl and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: firehouse chili
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Put meat in a 1-quart pot and add 2 cups water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for 2 hours.
Keep pot covered.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Have butter soft.
Add sugar and cream together well.
Add flour and eggs; beat well.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely before serving.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Fill slices of green peppers.
Chill and serve!

title: peanut butter chocolate balls
directions: Combine everything except chocolate morsels and shortening. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Combine chocolate morsels and shortening and melt in microwave for 5 to 6 minutes at 50% power.
Dip each peanut butter ball into chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper and cool.
Store in refrigerator.
(Can be frozen.)

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Microwave butter on high until melted, approx. 1 minute.
Stir milk and sugar into butter mixture until well blended.
Microwave on high for 5 minutes, stir halfway thru.
Microwave on high again for 5 1/2 minutes, stirring halfway thru.
Add chips slowly stirring constantly.
Add marshmallow creme and stir until blended. Add vanilla and nuts stirring until blended.
Pour into 13x9 greased pan (I use butter to grease it) and smooth out.
Let set at least 4 hours preferably overnight.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti. Let cool. Pour into large bowl. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in casserole dish.
Heat margarine, onion, rice, cheese and soup on stove until melted. Pour over broccoli and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together. Then roll in balls and in powdered sugar or granulated sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots 15 to 25 minutes or until carrots are just tender.
Meanwhile, melt in a skillet butter.
Add and stir in brown sugar.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Drain carrots thoroughly.
Dry carrots by shaking pan over low heat. Add to butter-sugar mixture in skillet.
Simmer a few minutes or until carrots are glazed.
Turn several times to glaze evenly. Makes 4 servings.
Double for larger servings.

title: special k cookies
directions: Put 5 cups Special K into a bowl.
Mix syrup and sugar in a pan; bring slowly to 30 second boil.
Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter.
Pour over Special K.
Shape size desired or put by tablespoon onto wax paper.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend ingredients together (beat with mixer).
Pour into pie shells and bake in a preheated 400° oven 7 minutes.
Lower oven temperature to 350° and bake for 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: noodles
directions: Beat egg, add baking powder, salt and water.
Add flour to make a stiff dough, roll out very thin, let set for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut to desired width, can be cooked at once or can be dried for several hours.
This can be doubled, I never make less than 2 eggs.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add milk, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour into 4 pie crusts and freeze. Makes 4 pies.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix in brown sugar and spread evenly.
Decorate with pineapple slices, cherries and nuts. In a separate bowl combine dry ingredients.
Mix together egg yolks with reserved pineapple syrup and add to dry mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour carefully over pineapple and cherries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top springs back when touched lightly with finger.
Tent with foil if browning too quickly.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix milk, pineapple and strawberry pie filling.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into dish and freeze.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Boil peas 5 minutes.
Arrange spinach in a deep glass bowl. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Add layers of lettuce, sliced eggs and olives.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar. Add layers of peas and bacon (drained and crumbled).
Top with mayonnaise to seal.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
Mix ingredients.
Serve with Hawaiian bread or with vegetables.

title: green chile chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to taste. Dredge in flour.
Fry in oil until browned.	Drain.	Mix cream of chicken soup with green chilies.
Place
chicken
in
a
casserole	dish.
Pour soup/chili mixture over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Place in a hot oven until cheese is bubbly and sauce is hot.

title: chocolate coconut chillers
directions: Line a 6-cup muffin tin with paper baking cups; place a chocolate wafer cookie in each cup. In a large bowl, combine the ice cream and coconut; mix well. Using an ice cream scoop, place a rounded scoopful of the ice cream mixture into each cup. Top each with the chopped almonds and freeze for 1 hour or until firm. Drizzle hard-shell topping over each until the tops are completely covered. Freeze until the chocolate is firm. Serve or cover and keep frozen until ready to serve.

title: french mint tea
directions: Combine tea,
mint
leaves and 1 quart water in a large saucepan.
Cover
and
bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Let steep
minutes. Add lemon juice, orange juice concentrate, sugar
and	additional
water to make 2 quarts liquid.
Strain and chill. Serve over ice.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Place rack in lowest position in oven.
Preheat oven to 425°. Spoon apple filling into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes. Meanwhile, melt 1/4 cup margarine.
Beat in sweetened milk, eggs, flavoring, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour over apples.
Combine sugar and flour; cut in remaining 1/4 cup margarine until crumbly.
Stir in granola.
Sprinkle over pie.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes or until set in center.
Cool.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple (undrained) and pie filling in 9 x 13-inch pan; mix together.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over mixture.
Dot with 1 stick butter.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes to 1 hour, until golden brown.

title: no peek beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Stir together well. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours or on High for 4 to 6 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: swedish pie
directions: Cream together egg, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with ice cream while warm.

title: vegetarian hamburgers
directions: Mix all the ingredients except oatmeal together and then fold in the oatmeal.
Fry by tablespoons as patties.
Make gravy and simmer burgers in it for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients, then sprinkle brown sugar, flour, pecans and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as package directs.
Place in casserole dish. Make sauce of soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs, which have been mixed with butter.
Bake until bubbly hot in 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: savory patties
directions: Combine meat, salt, onion, mustard, 1/4 cup crumbs, egg and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix very well and shape into 6 patties.
Put the 1/2 cup crumbs on a piece of waxed paper and press patties onto it so the crumbs adhere to the outside.
Heat the oil in a frypan. Brown patties on both sides.
Turn down heat.
Drain off any fat from pan.
Open soup and add 1/4 cup water.
Pour over patties. Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with cooked egg noodles. Sprinkle with chopped chives.
You can substitute turkey for all or part of beef.

title: rosemary and garlic roasted potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; cut in half or quarter.
Place in a covered microwave dish with 2 tablespoons water.
Cook on High for 2 minutes to slightly soften potatoes.
Drain.
Pour olive oil in a nonstick baking pan big enough to hold the potatoes in one layer. Rub the potatoes in the oil to coat on all sides.
Sprinkle with garlic and rosemary.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, uncovered, in a 450° oven for 30 minutes, turning the potatoes twice so that all sides are browned.
Serves 4.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Brown meat; drain.
Add onion, pepperoni, mushrooms, sauces and spices.
Mix with pasta; pour into casserole (makes two 8-inch square pans).
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: lite chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, unbeaten, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Combine milk, water and vanilla flavoring.
Alternate liquid and dry ingredients, adding to creamed mixture.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: corn puddin'
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake slowly for 1 hour.

title: cookies `n' creme
directions: Fix pudding according to directions.
Mix whipped topping, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Place crushed cookies on bottom of dish, spread with chocolate pudding.
Spread with cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle nuts and crushed cookies on top.

title: sweet and sour cabbage slaw
directions: Shred 1 large head cabbage and 4 carrots.
Add 1 large sweet pepper and 1 sweet onion, sliced thin.
Mix in large bowl and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix the first 5 ingredients, using 1 tablespoon of the sugar, and bring to a boil but do not boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture and let set for several days, at least 24 hours.

title: baked grits
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients by adding grits to boiling water containing salt and oleo.
Turn down to low and cook for 5 to 8 minutes (add milk to thin if necessary).
Add chili peppers, grated cheese and beaten egg.
Stir and cover.
Cook at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar plum pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: candied apples
directions: Core or pare apples.
Stick with cloves.
Cook sugar, water and cinnamon drops for 5 minutes.
Add apples and cook very slowly until tender, basting often with syrup in pan.
Serve with meat or very cold with whipped cream as dessert.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Chop up and mix together.
Pour Ranch dressing over and serve.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Sift flour and add spices.
Add dry ingredients gradually. Stir in vanilla, apples and nuts.
Pack into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 12.

title: layer lettuce salad
directions: Spread lettuce in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine celery, green pepper, onion and peas.
Mix well.
Spoon over lettuce.

title: betty's meat balls
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.
Brown in a little oil in frypan then put into roaster.

title: vegetable torte
directions: Cook spinach and sliced zucchini in small amount of oil. Transfer to a mixing bowl and mash. Stir in all of the other ingredients. Season to taste. Spread in an 8 x 8 or 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle top with some additional Parmesan cheese. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: clam bisque
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Stir in flour; cook and stir until bubbly, about 2 minutes.
Slowly stir in clams with their liquid.
Add clam juice.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in cream or mixture of milk and cream, tomato paste and lemon juice.
Heat slowly; do not boil.
May be refrigerated or frozen and reheated.

title: reuben loaf
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
In large bowl, mix remaining flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir in hot water and margarine.
Mix in only enough reserved flour to make soft dough.
On floured surface, knead 4 minutes.

title: kourabiedes
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy, about 15 minutes.
Add egg yolk and flour.
Beat until well blended.
Gradually add flour until the mixture holds shape (crescent round, etc.).
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until lightly brown.
Allow to cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Chop onions, pepper and pimento.
Combine with corn and other ingredients in order given.
Mix well and pour in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ultimate cheese burgers
directions: Combine dressing mix with beef and cheese. Shape into 4 patties; cook thoroughly. Serve on toasted buns.

title: impromptu appetizer
directions: Pour cocktail sauce over cream cheese.
Top with shrimp. Serve with crackers or party breads.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar and beat until well blended.
Add vanilla.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: strawberry banana dessert
directions: Layer banana slices and cake cubes in a 13x9x2- inch dish coated with non-stick spray.
Place strawberries over cake and press down gently.
In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in cold water.
Pour over strawberries.
Refrigerate for 3 hours, or until set.
Frost with whipped topping.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry onion, garlic, celery and green pepper in oil.
Remove from pan and add meat.
Cook, stirring frequently, until meat is brown.
Add vegetables and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Bring to a boil the milk, oleo and sugar.
Add the vanilla after taking off the stove. When cake is done and taken out of the oven, pour hot topping over cake.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Use 2 tablespoons per cup.

title: pineapple banana smoothee(beverage)
directions: Blend juice, dry milk and banana.
Add ice cream or sherbet. Blend until smooth.
Be creative!
Try different mixtures!

title: cheese specials
directions: In a saucepan melt 1/2 stick butter.
Slice tomatoes to desired thickness and spread out in a saucepan; sprinkle with garlic, salt, pepper and other spices, if desired.
Turn tomatoes and sprinkle again with desired spices.
Place several slices of cheese (Provolone) on top of sauteed tomatoes.
When melted, put onto fresh or toasted Italian bread or rolls.

title: hot potato-celery salad
directions: Cook bacon.
Remove from pan and break into pieces.
Cook onions until tender in bacon drippings.
Blend in soup, milk, pickle relish, vinegar and bacon bits.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Serve hot.
Yields 6 servings.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
In a large mixing bowl, beat together cream cheese and sugar until smooth and light.
Beat in the eggs, vanilla, and cornstarch - only until thoroughly mixed. Stir in sour cream until mixture is well blended.
Pour the mixture into a prepared graham cracker crust and bake for 45 minutes. Allow to cool in the oven with door propped slightly open for 3 hours.
Chill.
Can top with favorite fruit pie filling.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: In a large bowl combine cucumbers, peppers and onions.
In a small bowl combine sugar, salt, celery seed, mustard seed and vinegar; blend well.
Pour over cucumber mixture; toss to coat well.
Cover; refrigerate for at least 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
If desired, drain before serving.
Makes 3 cups.

title: lemon coconut cake
directions: Cream fat and sugar; add well beaten egg yolks and add sifted dry ingredients alternately with water and lemon juice or milk. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in three layers in moderate oven 15 to 20 minutes.
When cool, put together with Lemon Coconut Filling and sprinkle with coconut.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Beat all together for 5 minutes.
Pour into well oiled tube pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: jo's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and brown sugar with margarine.
Beat in eggs. Add peanut butter.
Gradually add dry ingredients and vanilla. Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Slightly press with fork dipped in flour.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In bowl, blend sugar and butter.
Add eggs and sour cream plus vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to blended mix.
After adding flour, beat with mixer for 10 minutes.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix altogether; shape into 2 loaves.
Cover with foil.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Take foil off; cook 15 more minutes, until browned on top.
Can freeze.

title: salmon rice medley
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Saute onion, garlic and curry in oleo. Drain salmon. Break into large chunks.
Chop eggs. In an 8-inch baking dish, combine eggs, fish, rice medley and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: southern rice
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil.
Add water, rice, bouillon, and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes, until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Stir in parsley.
Serves 6-8.
Recipe can be halved.

title: belinda's crawfish fettucine
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Add milk.
Keep simmering and add flour gradually.
Add cheese and crawfish.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes stirring occasionally.
Boil noodles until tender.
Add noodles to crawfish.
Season to taste.
Place in overproof dish. Top with more cheese.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: no peek stew
directions: Prepare meat and vegetables.
Cut or slice the size you like. Put
all
ingredients
into
a large pot.
Cover with a tight lid or foil.
Cook 4 to 6 hours at 250° or until vegetables are tender.

title: golden potato soup
directions: Wash, peel and dice potato.
Boil potatoes in 2 to 3 quarts of water until tender.
Dissolve bouillon in small amount of hot water and add to potatoes.
Slice carrot and celery.
Dice onion. (Microwave carrot, celery and onion for 1 to 2 minutes to reduce cooking time.)
Add to potatoes.
Dissolve flour in small amount of water and add to pot to thicken broth.
Add milk.
When soup is hot again, add cheese, salt and pepper.
Cooking time: approximately 45 minutes.
Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Puree onion and green pepper in blender or food processor. (If too dry to puree, add a small amount of water.)
Wet bread; do not soak.
Squeeze out excess water from bread.
Mix puree with bread (it will look like a green blob).
Mix together meat, salt, pepper and puree mixture.
Mixture should not be too wet or too dry.
If meat is too wet, add more bread.
If meat is too dry, add a little water.
Roll meat into small balls and brown in skillet.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix as instructed.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan, greased; layer pecans, then coconut in bottom of pan.
Pour cake mix over pecans and coconut.
Soften cream cheese and margarine.
Mix powdered sugar with cream cheese and margarine.
Pour over top of all.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and milk.
Add vanilla. Add baking powder to flour and sift; stir into creamed mixture. Dough should be stiff.
Roll to 1/4-inch thick; cut out with any cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: red beans & rice
directions: Saut sausage, onions, celery, green pepper, & garlic in butter in a large skillet until tender.
Stir beans into vegetables and add seasoning.
Salt to taste.
Simmer 30 - 40 minutes, remove bay leaves.
Serve over rice.

title: potato casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.	Wash potatoes thoroughly.
Peel and slice
potatoes.
Place
half
of
potato slices in dish. Cover with
half	the
sliced onion and 1 roll of cheese.
Dot with a little butter, salt and pepper.
Repeat layer.
Bake at 375 °, covered.
Time of preparation: 45 minutes.	Serves 4 to 6.

title: buddy's apple pie
directions: Stir the last 4 ingredients and pour over the apples.
Dot with butter and cinnamon (optional).
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked or boiled custard
directions: Stir sugar into eggs; add warm milk and vanilla.
Pour in fireproof dish, adding margarine, flaked in tiny pieces, and nutmeg on top.
Stand dish in oven in tin of hot water or on asbestos mat to prevent curdling.
Stir custard before it sets so that margarine is well mixed with other ingredients.
(GE)

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Pour in oil; add pumpkin pie mix, cranberry sauce and water; blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Pour into well greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 large or 3 small loaves.

title: dump cake
directions: You will also need 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 2/3 cup boiling water; break cream cheese into small pieces.
Add juice of oranges and pineapple.
Mix well. Add fruit, coconut and marshmallows to jello.
Last then, chill overnight.
Before serving, add one 8 ounce Cool Whip.

title: rice porridge
directions: Put
directly in pan and bring to boil slowly, stirring frequently.
When
it
comes
to
a
boil,	cover with lid and simmer for 1 hour.	It will thicken.
Serve with butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.

title: fruit salad dessert
directions: Mix together lightly and chill in icebox.
For variety, add nuts, fruits or coconut.

title: yeast bread squares
directions: Combine yeast and warm water in a large bowl. Add shortening, sugar, salt, and 2 cups flour. Beat 3 minutes at low speed of mixer. Stir in remaining flour.

title: honey carrots
directions: Heat 1 inch salted water to boiling.
Add carrots.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Cook and stir the remaining ingredients in 10 inch skillet until bubbly.
Add carrots.
Cook uncovered over low heat, stirring occasionally, until carrots are glazed.

title: chocolate marshmallow squares
directions: Put in double boiler.
Stir until melted.
Slightly cool 5 minutes.
Add 3 1/2 cups marshmallows (miniature).
Put graham crackers in bottom of buttered dish.
Cool.
Turn upside-down to cut.

title: seven-layer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle the graham cracker crumbs over the bottom of a square 9-inch baking pan.
Pour the melted butter or margarine over the crumbs.
Sprinkle on the chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and walnuts.
Then pour the condensed milk over everything.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until the mixture is light brown around the edges.
Don't overbake the cookies or they will dry out.
Refrigerate the cookies in the pan for about 30 minutes.
Then cut into small squares.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and allspice. Add apples; toss to coat fruit.
Transfer to a 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: mustard-glazed shrimp
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Combine the Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Add the cream cheese and cherry pie filling; mix at low speed.
Makes two 9 x 9-inch dishes or one 9 x 12-inch dish.
(I usually freeze this dessert for a quick frozen dessert.
It is also good not frozen.)

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender. Add all remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings (2 quarts).

title: spaghetti balduini rome, italy(serves 6)
directions: In a large frying pan, saute olive oil, onion and butter until onions are golden brown.
Add garlic, tomatoes and salt.
Simmer slowly for 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/4 cup of the stuffing mix. Spoon into a lightly greased 3-quart casserole.
Top with the remaining stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry bars
directions: Beat sugar, butter, margarine and eggs until well blended. Add lemon juice and flour.
Pour batter into ungreased baking pan. Pour cherries on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut in squares.

title: corned beef sandwiches
directions: Mix all together and
add
mayonnaise, enough to spread easily.
Good on wheat or white bread.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil,
chocolate and sugar.
Beat in 1 egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to chocolate mixture.
Mix well.

title: broccoli cheese soup with fideos
directions: Heat water; add bouillon cubes.
Thaw and drain frozen broccoli.
Break pasta into 3-inch pieces.
Combine all ingredients and cook slowly.

title: sugarless fruit salad
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle pudding and gelatin over mixture.
Mix well and cover.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: buns
directions: Mix yeast with water and warm milk.
Then take flour, sugar, salt, oil and eggs.
Mix together with water and milk mixture. Let rise, then punch down and let rise again.
Next, put on baking sheet in rolls and let rise on sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 14 minutes.
This recipe is also good for pepperoni rolls.

title: sour milk waffles
directions: Beat eggs; add milk.
Add sifted flour with soda and baking powder.
Add other dry ingredients. Add melted butter.
If used for pancakes, have skillet hot enough for a drop of water to jump around in pan.
Pour 1/4 cup of mix in pan.
Cook until bubbles form on top and turn until brown.

title: rise-and-shine biscuits
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream and club soda in a medium bowl, stirring well.
Add biscuit mix, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead 10 to 12 times.
Shape dough with hands into 6 biscuits about 1-inch thick.
Place 1 biscuit in the center of a lightly greased 8-inch round cake pan.
Arrange remaining biscuits in a circle around the center one.
Bake at 450° for 16 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
(May make thinner biscuits and bake for a shorter time, if preferred.)

title: mom's tea cakes
directions: Mix
all dry ingredients, then add eggs and sour cream. Next, add
the
lard
and
mix well. Roll out 1/2-inch thick. Bake in a moderate oven at 350°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter cream cheese pie
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter and milk, beating until smooth and creamy.
Fold topping into peanut butter mixture.
Pour into prepared shell and chill for 5 to 6 hours.
May garnish with coarsely chopped peanuts.

title: pumpkin chiffon dessert
directions: Combine gingersnap crumbs and butter and stir well.
Press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine cream cheese, eggs and sugar.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth. Spread over crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.

title: crockpot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Spray crockpot with Pam spray. Mix other ingredients. Put in crockpot. Cook on low 3
1/2 to 4 hours. Do not open lid until done.

title: chili beans
directions: Chop up the onion and pepper; put all ingredients into a crock-pot.
Let simmer for 2 hours on medium.

title: poor man's chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa and soda together 3 times.
Mix mayo, boiling water and vanilla; beat for 2 minutes.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch or
2 (8-inch) round pans.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bread
directions: Dissolve yeast cakes in 3/4 cup potato water.
Add seven cups flour and beat batter well.
Add more flour (it takes about 6 pounds.)
Makes 6 loaves.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken; debone and drain.
In another pan, cook combined soups, water, onion and mushrooms; bring to a simmer.
Add salsa and Velveeta.
When cheese is melted, add chicken.
To serve, pour chicken mixture over crushed tortillas.

title: pepperidge party rye
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread on party rye or pumpernickel and place under broiler until bubbles form on top and slightly browned.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in a tight container. To serve, use 2 tablespoons to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Blend together; add strawberries last.
Cook at 350° until done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fair tacos
directions: In a skillet, slowly cook ground beef until lightly browned. Add minced garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Drain off excess fat. Add minced green onions, chopped lettuce and mashed potatoes; simmer for 7 minutes.
In hot oil, heat tortillas one at a time, just until softened.
Put meat mixture into each tortilla.
Enjoy.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, 1/4 cup at a time, salt, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Beat very stiff and fold in nuts and chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave in oven until cool (about 2 hours) or overnight.

title: chili con queso
directions: In a medium saucepan cook onion in butter or margarine until tender but not brown.
Stir in tomatoes, chili peppers and salt. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add cheeses, a little at a time, stirring just until melted.
Stir in a little milk if mixture becomes too thick.
Heat through over low heat.
Transfer to a small serving bowl.
Serve warm with tortilla chips or corn chips.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: snowballs(chocolate filled)
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light.
Add flour and nuts; blend well and chill.
Shape dough around kisses using 1 tablespoon of dough for each kiss.
Roll to make a ball.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 minutes or until set but not brown.
Cool slightly, while still warm.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa.
Add oleo and milk; cook over medium heat until boiling for 45 seconds to 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
When mixed well, add oatmeal.
Mix well, let cool about 2 to 4 minutes and spoon onto foil.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a shallow 2 qt casserole.
Cook the spinach according to the package directions.
Drain well. Place in mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 cup melted butter, cream cheese and lemon juice.
Blend well with a fork.
Scatter artichoke quarters evenly over the bottom of the casserole dish.
Cover with the spinach mixture and smooth the top.
Cover the top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Drizzle with 1 tbsp melted butter.
Bake on the middle rack until bubbly in the center and lightly brown on the top, approx. 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and serve.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake or toss in bowl until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Discard bag.

title: grandma's jello
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of water. Set until firm enough to whip.
Prepare Dream Whip.
Drain pineapple and mix with softened cream cheese.
Blend whipped jello and the Dream Whip.
Add cream cheese and pineapple.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Double for 9 x 13-inch recipe.

title: 125 year old black walnut pound cake
directions: Grease tube pan.
Cream together butter and shortening.
Mix sugar in well.
Add one egg at a time.
Add flavorings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Meringue can be omitted.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: great northern beans
directions: Brown bacon. Cut into small pieces. Put the Great Northern beans, sour cream, brown sugar and the bacon together on low until it thickens, about 2 hours. I add cornstarch to thicken. Enjoy.

title: chocolate cream cheesecake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on package.
Set aside. Mix together next 4 ingredients, then add the last 3 ingredients. Beat on high speed until smooth.
Spread 1/2 of cake mix into greased and floured sheet pan.
Spread cheese mixture evenly over batter.
Top with remaining batter.
Spread to cover cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: grandma norma's flaky pastry
directions: Mix and chill overnight or several hours.
Roll and cut into triangle, into a small crescent shape.
Bake 12 minutes at 425° (until golden brown).
When cooled, frost.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in bowl; mix well. Shape into balls by tablespoon. Place in ungreased 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Combine tomato sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce in bowl; mix well. Spoon over meatballs. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes longer.

title: scalloped cabbage with cheese
directions: Cook cabbage; grease baking dish.
Put a layer of cabbage, then sprinkle a layer of cheese, then a layer of white sauce. Layer ingredients until finished.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven until crumbs are brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli with olive oil and browned garlic over penne*
directions: In a large skillet, heat the olive oil and garlic over medium-high heat until the garlic turns a light golden color, 2 or 3 minutes.
Add the broccoli and saute until it is dark green and tender-crisp, about 3 minutes.
Immediately spoon the broccoli, garlic and oil over cooked pasta.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cover raisins with water; simmer until tender.
Use 9 tablespoons of liquid from raisins.
Add soda and shortening; cool.
Mix sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Then add flour, cinnamon and salt.
Add oats, raisins and chocolate chips.
Drop by large tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown in 350° oven.

title: rhubarb dream bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Then beat eggs and add to the rhubarb mix. Put on top of crust and bake for 30 minutes at 350° in 7 x 10-inch pan.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Place blueberries evenly in bottom of well-greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Cream sugar and butter together.
Add milk alternately with flour, baking powder and salt which have been sifted together.
Mix well and smooth the batter carefully and evenly over blueberries in pan.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Blend thoroughly so cornstarch will not lump.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Pour boiling water over all but do not stir.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
If top begins to brown too much, lower heat for last 15 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: microwave nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine tomatoes, soup and cheese in large glass bowl.
Microwave until all is blended together.
Add ground beef.
Ready to serve with chips or crackers.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Alternate with milk to first mixture.
Add vanilla and bake in large tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add Cheddar cheese into bowl with hamburger mixture.

title: crepes
directions: Beat with whip.
Pour in greased hot pan and tilt to spread thin.
Takes about a minute each side.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put milk in saucepan and heat.
Put in bread cubes and butter.
In large bowl put sugar, salt, raisins and eggs; mix well.
Blend all together; add lemon flavoring.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Place dish in pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Combine squash, onion, margarine, salt, pepper, beaten egg, milk, cheese and 1/2 cup crackers.
Place in Pam coated casserole dish.
Place in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining crackers on top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Add together the pudding, jello, tapioca and 4 cups liquid drained from the fruit. Bring to a boil. Cool. Drain fruit and add water to make 4 cups
for first mixture.
Add fruit to cooled pudding.
Refrigerate.
Serve in a bowl or dish.
Not good for molds.
Makes lots!

title: seafoam nut bars
directions: Blend together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Do not sift; set aside.
Cream 1/2 cup brown sugar, granulated sugar, margarine, egg yolks and vanilla thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients; mix well.
Press into 2 well-greased 9-inch square pans.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add 1 1/2 cups brown sugar gradually, continuing to beat until soft peaks are formed. Spread evenly over mixture in pans.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.
Cool in pans on racks.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and place in bottom of baking dish.
Add a layer of onions and Tater Tots and cover with soup mixed with milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pea salad
directions: Use most of the vegetable juices.

title: chocolate coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients real well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
(Makes 2 pies.)

title: apple pie filling
directions: Peel the apples and cut into small slices.
Mix the sliced apples with the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, flour and salt in a pan and stir until well blended.
Set aside.
Blend egg yolks and milk until smooth and add to cocoa mixture.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until filling poofs up and looks dry on top and crust has browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with 1/2 bag Pepperidge Farm cornbread stuffing mix.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. If topping becomes too brown, cover with foil.

title: perfect peach pie
directions: Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tomato aspic salad
directions: Bring tomato juice to a boil.
Remove from heat; add jello and stir well.
Cover and chill until consistency of egg white.
Stir in water, celery and onion.
Cover with foil.
(Lightly oil container you put it in.)

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken with onions; debone.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute onions and bell pepper in oleo.
Add to spaghetti. Add diced chicken.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add peas, tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour in casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple bread stuffing
directions: Cube the bread.
Melt 1 stick of butter in a pan and put 1/2 of the cubed bread in the pan.
Toss until browned.
Remove from the pan.
Repeat this procedure to the rest of the bread cubes and second stick of butter.
Beat eggs, sugar and pineapple with pineapple juice.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Spread in browned cubes evenly.
Pour liquid over cubes.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Wonderful to serve with a fresh baked ham.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix instant pudding, pineapple juice and Tang.
Beat well.
Add mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks and refrigerate overnight. Next day, add more fruit (bananas, blueberries, strawberries, grapes, fruit cocktail, drained, etc.).
Chill.
(The Tang keeps bananas from turning brown.)
Don't add cherries.
This is best made the day before.
Keeps a few days in refrigerator.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix crumbs, butter and 1/4 cup of sugar together.
Line bottom of dish with half of crumbs.
Beat Dream Whip and milk until thick.
Cream the cheese and 1/2 cup of sugar.
add to Dream Whip and mix.
Pat layer of whip then layer of cherries, then a layer of remaining crumbs.

title: sour cream sugared pecans
directions: Mix sugar, salt and sour cream, cook over low heat until hard ball forms in cold water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Add nuts and stir until well coated.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet to dry.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Trim off thin layer of fat from meat.
Sprinkle with pepper. Rub paste mixture all over roast.
Put rosemary stalk on top of meat to bake.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°, uncovered, until meat thermometer registers 175° internal temperature.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Spread in a 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Spread with chili sauce and bake 15 minutes longer. Cool for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from pan and slice.

title: mexican jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour half of mix into greased skillet.
Sprinkle half of the cheese over batter; add remaining batter and sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Using a blender, combine the milk, sugar, Bisquick mix, eggs, butter and vanilla. Cover and blend on low for 3 minutes. Pour into a greased deep dish glass pie dish. Let set for 5 minutes. Then sprinkle coconut evenly over the pie. Bake for 40 minutes. Serve warm or cold.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Sprinkle any combination of raw vegetables over cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: pear honey
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours, until thick like honey. Pour in hot jars and seal.

title: asparagus and pea casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, layer half of asparagus, peas, eggs and cheese.
Repeat with other half.
Mix sour cream, onion powder, mushroom soup and black pepper.
Pour over layered mixture, spreading all over.
Mix together melted margarine and bread crumbs and sprinkle over top.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: nippy carrots
directions: Boil carrots.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir gently.
Cook over low heat for about 5 minutes to glaze.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Save broth; add onions, bell peppers, celery, butter and spaghetti. Boil until spaghetti is done; add soup, cheese and chicken to noodles.
Stir constantly until cheese is completely melted.

title: mom's eggplant spread
directions: Cut eggplant in half; place in baking pan, skin side up. Bake at 375° until slightly burnt.
Remove and cool, then scrape pulp from the skin; set aside.

title: just like mrs. field's cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
In the blender, process oatmeal to a fine powder.
In a separate bowl, blend together the oatmeal powder, flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a 375° oven for approximately
9 to 10 minutes.
Let cookies set on a cookie sheet for a minute and remove to cooling rack.
They do not look like they are done when taken from the oven.

title: company round steak
directions: Pound steak and cut into serving size pieces.
Brown in small amount of shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add soup, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add onion.
Cook 30 minutes more.
Add tomato wedges; heat.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple dip
directions: Beat together and dip apples.

title: pig nuts
directions: Cut bacon strips in half.
Wrap bacon around 1/2 or 1 whole chestnut.
Layer in baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Drain fat from dish.
Mix brown sugar, salad dressing and chili sauce.
Pour over chestnuts.
Return to oven for 15 minutes.
Very Good!

title: ambrosia fruit cups
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons of juice (discard the remaining juice).
Place pineapple and juice in a bowl; add remaining ingredients and toss lightly.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: chicken fried round steak
directions: Pound steak to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut in 6 serving size pieces. Blend egg and milk.
Combine cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Dip meat in egg mixture, then crumbs.
In a 12-inch skillet, slowly brown meat in hot oil, turning once.
Cover tightly; cook over low heat until meat is tender, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: lady baltimore cake(lamb)
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Stir shortening to soften. Mix in dry ingredients.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes. Fold in beaten egg whites and beat for 1 minute.

title: marble squares
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda and set aside.
Mix remainder of ingredients together, then add flour mixture.
Stir in 1/2 cup nuts.
Spread in greased pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over mixture and press in.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: *Spicy - use El Poto sauce.

title: pineapple glazed apple pie
directions: In large saucepan, combine pineapple juice, 1/2 cup apple juice and the sugar.
Bring to boiling.
Blend the remaining 1/4 cup apple juice into cornstarch or flour.
Add to hot pineapple-apple liquid in saucepan.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add in apples and cook until near tender. Remove from heat; stir in margarine, vanilla and lemon flavorings, salt and allspice or apple pie spice.

title: elk stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into thin strips (like French fries).
Roll in flour and pepper (always salt wild meat after it has been cooked on both sides as the salt draws all the moisture out and leaves it tasteless).
Brown in butter or oil.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic.
When browned, stir in beef broth.
Cover and cook 1 hour until tender.
Stir in sour cream.
Simmer 5 minutes more.
Very good served over hot homemade buttered noodles.

title: texas torte
directions: Add flour, salt and milk to eggs.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a flat well-greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve hot.

title: baked crab in shell
directions: Saute diced onion, celery and pepper in butter.
In bowl, mix cracker crumbs, cream and seasonings to taste.
Add sauteed vegetables and crab meat.
Fill crab shells and top with paprika. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Garnish with lemon.

title: corn salad
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Dice fine.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables and let set overnight.
Serves 6.

title: punch
directions: Very good with orange, grape or strawberry.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar. Combine with remaining ingredients. Pour into shallow unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken sandwiches
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook green pepper, celery and onion until tender. Add chicken and barbecue sauce. Heat through, stirring occasionally. Serve over buns.

title: easy crumb cake
directions: Mix the last 3 ingredients for crumbs first and set aside. Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Alternate flour, baking powder and milk (vanilla in milk).
Pour into 2 lightly greased and floured 8 or 9-inch pans.
Sprinkle crumbs and bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: southern decadence
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using mixer, beat eggs; add flour and sugars slowly until well blended.
Add melted margarine, chocolate chips, coconut, nuts and bourbon.
Stir until mixture is smooth. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°, then 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool to room temperature.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and spread approximately 2 cups in bottom of oblong pan.
Cream the cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla until blended.
Combine pudding mix and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Gently fold cheese and pudding mixes together.
Pour mixture over cookies.
Top with remaining cookie crumbs.
Cover with foil. Refrigerate.

title: wassail
directions: Heat cider or apple juice and cinnamon stick to boiling. Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover and add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer an additional 5 minutes.
Serves 15 to 16 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: tex-mex corn chowder
directions: Combine cream corn, whole kernel corn, tomatoes (undrained), broth and water in saucepan. Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes. Sprinkle each serving with shredded
cheddar cheese or chopped chili peppers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, vanilla, oil, sugar and zucchini.
Add flour, raisins and nuts.
Oil and flour two loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fun potatoes
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze well.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage. Break
up
and
drain. Remove crust from bread and cut
in
cubes.
Mix sausage, bread and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt	and
dry mustard.
Pour over sausage mixture in lightly greased
9	x 9-inch pan or Bundt pan.
Refrigerate overnight.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend together sharp shredded Cheddar cheese and butter. Blend in flour, Tabasco sauce, salt and paprika.
Drain the olives and wrap cheese mixture around olives.
Freeze on baking sheets. Store in plastic bags.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes frozen.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake until cheese is melted about 15 minutes.

title: baked ham puffs
directions: Cut out small rounds from fresh bread, about 40.
Toast rounds on one side under the broiler.
Blend together all ingredients. Spread untoasted side of bread round with deviled ham (2 large cans) and cover with mound of cheese mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until puffed and brown. Serve hot.

title: chewy nut squares
directions: Mix 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar.
Cut in margarine until fine crumbs form.
Pack into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Mix flour, sugar and remaining ingredients.
Pour over crust.
Bake 30 minutes until top sets. Cool at least 1 hour.
Cut into 16 squares.
(Start with middle.)

title: christmas punch
directions: Place in a large pan and heat.
Serve hot.

title: potato pancakes
directions: In a large bowl, place the raw, shredded potatoes.
Mix in flour and salt.
Incorporate eggs and mix until thoroughly blended.
Heat enough oil in frying pan to make about 1/4 inch thick.
Drop heaping spoonfuls of potato mixture and drop into the sizzling shortening.
Flatten each spoonful until pancake is shaped.

When bottom side is golden brown and potato shreds are looking crisp on the edges, turn carefully to the other side. When golden brown underneath, take from pan and transfer to a paper towel lined cookie sheet.
To keep warm until all pancakes are fried, place in a 325 degree oven.
Serve with applesauce.

title: beet jelly
directions: Boil juice and Sure-Jell hard for 5 minutes.
Add the sugar and boil hard for 10 minutes.
Add Kool-Aid.
Pour into sterilized jars.

title: beet jelly
directions: Bring beet juice and lemon juice to a boil.
Add pectin and bring to a full boil.
Add sugar and boil until it jells (5 to 7 minutes).
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Do not double recipe.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: debbie's rocks
directions: Seed and cut dates.
Break nuts into large pieces.
Add together in large container (dishpan) and mix well with flour. Cream butter; add sugar gradually until well creamed.
Add spices. Beat egg slightly and blend with mixture.
Add soda-water and pour over date and nut mixture.
Mix thoroughly and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Makes about 250 rocks.

title: lentil soup
directions: Mix all the ingredients and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Easy to make.
The cumin is a must for the soup!

title: orange chicken
directions: Skin and debone chicken breasts. Place in bottom of microwave dish. Combine remaining ingredients and cook until slightly thickened. Pour over the chicken and cover with glass lid. Microwave on 3/4 power level (7 or 8) for 20 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter. Add boiling water, vegetable cube and soup stock.
Pour into individual crocks.
Top with croutons and cheeses.
Put in a 375° oven for 10 minutes or until lightly browned or melted on top.

title: bacon potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes, carrots, celery and onions. Cook until tender. Add evaporated skim milk, butter-flavored seasoning, salt, pepper and chives. Simmer 5 minutes. Stir in mashed potato mix. Add Canadian bacon and simmer 30 minutes. You may add more liquid if you prefer. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: In a saucepan melt the oleo or butter and cheese.
Sift together the sugar and cocoa and add oleo-cheese mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add nuts, if desired.
Mix well.

title: taco dip for chips
directions: Spread cream cheese into medium sized microwave-safe bowl. Add chili as next layer.
Spread cheese on top.
Microwave until cheese is melted and mix is hot.
Serve with taco chips as a dip.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and carrots into small pieces.
Mix all other ingredients.
Add cauliflower, carrots and lettuce.

title: broccoli, rice and chicken casserole
directions: Boil broccoli with 1/4 cup onion until tender.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
Saute remaining onion, green pepper and celery in 1/2 stick oleo until tender.
Mix the soup, milk and cheese.
Add rice and chicken.
Pour the soup mix over all.
Top with bread crumbs which have been mixed with 1/2 stick oleo.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, mushrooms and taco seasoning in large heavy pot.
Cook until done; drain well and place in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients except picante sauce and tortilla chips. Toss lightly.
Serve over tortilla chips topped with picante sauce.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash
avocados
in medium size bowl.
Add lemon juice, salt and
pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning in another bowl.

title: chess squares
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites stiff.
Melt oleo.
Add sugars and cream.
Add egg yolks, cream again.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add flour to oleo and sugars.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Add nuts.
Grease and flour oblong cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: honey glaze for baked ham
directions: In a saucepan, combine mustard and cornstarch.
Stir in honey and lemon juice and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Lower heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Brush glaze over baking ham several times during the last minutes in the oven.
Makes enough for 7 to 10 pound ham.
Glaze gives a sheen to ham surface.

title: confetti slaw
directions: Toss the slaw mix with the onion slices. Combine remaining ingredients. Shake well to blend and pour over vegetables. This needs to cure at least 48 hours in the fridge before serving and it should be stirred up at least twice. Will keep 10 days in the fridge. Serves 12. Since it is mayonnaise-free, it is perfect for picnics and potlucks.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread beans on bottom of large plate.
Mash avocados and mix with lemon juice; spread over beans.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning and spread over avocados.
Spoon tomatoes over sour cream mixture, then spoon onions over tomatoes. Top with cheese.
Chill before serving.

title: kraut and beer fudge cake
directions: Cream
butter
with
sugar.
Beat
in eggs and vanilla. Sift dry
ingredients;
add
alternately with beer to egg mixture. Stir
in kraut.
Turn into 2 greased and floured 8-inch pans. Bake
in
oven for 40 minutes or cake tests done. Cool on racks, then frost with chocolate or vanilla icing.
If preferred, bake in tube pan for 60 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Boil jello and pineapple until jello is dissolved, approximately 2 to 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix buttermilk, Cool Whip, oranges and nuts.
Add to jello mixture and congeal.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes on medium heat.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour in greased and floured tube pan.
This cake can be any flavor you want.
Cherry jello & cherry nectar or lemon jello & lemon nectar.

title: cool 'n easy strawberry pie
directions: Stir boiling water into Jell-O in large bowl for 2 minutes. Add ice cubes to cold water, then add to Jell-O. Stir until ice is melted. Add Cool Whip. Mix until well blended. Refrigerate mixture until very thick and will mound. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: festive cranberry salad
directions: Make Jell-O according to directions on box.
Add 1 cup sugar and stir until dissolved.
Place mixture in refrigerator.

title: apple apricot crumble(easy)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the apple slices and apricots; place in a lightly buttered 10-inch gratin dish.
In a food processor, combine the flour, cinnamon, sugar and butter until the mixture resembles bread crumbs.
Spoon over the fruit.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until topping is golden.
Serve immediately with cream or custard.
Serves 6 to 8.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli and mix together with rest of ingredients.
Slice cheese and mix together.
Bake on 350° until hot.
About 20 minutes.

title: german farmers breakfast
directions: Fry bacon.
Cook onion in fat until tender.
Stir in cooked potatoes and cook until golden.
Combine bacon, parsley, eggs, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour egg mixture over potato-onion. Cook over low heat until eggs are set.
While cooking, slip a knife underneath to let wet mixture run under.
Flip over (cut first).
Add optional vegetables just before flipping.
When cooked, cut in wedges.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix all together.
This can be put in a bowl to be passed or spread in a cake pan and cut into squares.

title: pineapple pecan spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: easy crock-pot chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
May be cooked overnight or all day if you have to go to work.
Adjust the seasonings as you prefer.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together, pour into a greased baking dish and cover with topping.

title: egg pastry for deep dish pie
directions: Combine flour and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Combine water, egg and vinegar and add to flour mixture. Stir with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Shape dough into a ball and chill.
Divide dough into 2 equal portions.
Roll each portion to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface. Use for making a 2-crust deep dish pie (such as Upside-Down Apple Pie) or for 2 single crust, deep dish pie shells.

title: meatballs and sausage in sauce
directions: Put spaghetti sauce in slow cooker on low.
Precook sausage until done.
Mix all ingredients together.
Make meatballs and cook until cooked through.
Put sausage and meatballs in slow cooker for 4 to 6 hours.
Serve on hard rolls or over pasta.

title: gold water beans
directions: Soak beans overnight; cook until tender.
Brown meat and onion; add all ingredients to beans.
Simmer until flavor is blended, about 1 hour.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve over shredded lettuce.

title: preachers delight
directions: Crush wafers and spread half in buttered pan.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs well.
Pour this mixture over the crumbs.
Over this, spread whipped cream, sweetened a bit.
Over the cream, spread the crushed pineapple.
Cover with remaining wafer crumbs. Let refrigerate overnight.
Cut in squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: reggies beans
directions: 1. Wash and sort through beans. Soak overnight. Discard that water.
Add fresh water to cover beans.
2. Add all ingredients, bring to a boil, then reduce heat,
cover, and cook slowly for 2-3 hours stirring often.
Add water if needed.

title: raisin scones
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Using a pastry blender or fork, cut in butter.
Mixture should be crumbly.
Add raisins.
Add evaporated milk and eggs, one at a time.
Put on floured board and knead dough gently, 4 or 5 times. Press into 8-inch circle about 1-inch thick.
Place on cookie sheet and cut into 8 wedges (do not separate the wedges).
Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook until golden brown.
Serves warm.
Makes 8 pieces.

title: cabbage and beef casserole
directions: Shred cabbage and put in bottom of casserole dish.
Combine oil and onion in a Dutch oven, saute until tender and add to ground meat.
Cook until meat begins to brown.
Add rice, soup and water; mix well.
Then pour meat mixture over cabbage.
Do not stir.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: moon cake
directions: Cream butter, egg yolks, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle walnuts on top.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cut with thin-rimmed glass.
First cut will be round. Make second cut halfway through first cut, etc.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: potato and mushroom soup casserole
directions: Slice potatoes; place in buttered casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until brown at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal fruit cookies
directions: Roll into balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: foolproof rice casserole
directions: Put all in casserole. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water until tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Place macaroni in buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Heat milk, add cheese and stir until melted.
Stir beaten egg into macaroni.
Add salt and pepper to cheese mixture and mix into macaroni.
Cover with buttered crumbs and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rabbit in bag
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in a small size (10 x 16-inch) Brown-in-Bag.
Add rabbit pieces and shake gently to coat.
Spread out rabbit quarters in bottom of bag.
Add onion, celery and butter.
Combine wine and Kitchen Bouquet; add to bag.
Secure bag with twist-tie and make several 1/2-inch slits in bag.
Cook 1 hour or until tender.
Spoon the sauce over the rabbit in serving dish.

title: scalloped asparagus
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons of butter. Add flour, salt and pepper to make a smooth paste.
Drain asparagus. Add enough milk to liquid to make 2 cups of liquid. Cook until thickened.
Add pimento. Cover bottom of a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish with half of the asparagus, sliced eggs and cheese. Repeat with remaining ingredients. Top with bread crumbs.
Melt remaining butter and pour over top. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: woodford pudding
directions: Dissolve soda in milk.
Mix butter and sugar; add eggs.
Sift flour and cinnamon together.
Add milk and flour alternately. Blend in jam last.
Bake in 325° oven in ungreased cake pan for 45 minutes to 55 minutes.
Serve with Butterscotch Sauce.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Combine first seven ingredients; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover; chill several hours. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° in greased dish or pan for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cover for first 1/2 hour, remove cover and brown.

title: my favorite blueberry pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat first three ingredients at medium speed of a mixer until well-blended (about 5 minutes).

Add eggs and egg white, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Lightly spoon flour into dry measuring cups; level with a knife. Combine 2 tablespoons flour and blueberries in a small bowl; toss well.
Combine remaining flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with yogurt, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Fold in blueberry mixture and vanilla; pour cake batter into a 10-inch tube pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: old fashioned baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cook macaroni as package directs, decreasing time to 3 minutes; drain.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted oleo together. Set 1 cup of mixture aside. Pat remaining mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan. Slice bananas and layer over crust. (If you prefer, you can eliminate this layer and serve dessert with a couple slices of bananas on top; some people prefer this to the frozen bananas.) Slice ice cream 1/2 inch thick. Put over banana layer. Sprinkle with nuts and freeze until firm. Melt chocolate chips and 1/2 cup oleo; add 2 cups powdered sugar and 1 1/2 cups evaporated milk. Cook until thick and smooth. Stir constantly. Remove from heat; add vanilla. Cool and pour over ice cream. Freeze until firm. Whip the cream until stiff; sweeten if desired. Spread over chocolate layer. Top with reserved graham cracker crumbs. Store in freezer. Remove 10 minutes before serving.
Will keep in freezer for several weeks.

title: lemon drops
directions: Combine cake mix, Cool Whip, egg and lemon juice and peel.
Mix well (do not overmix).
Roll into small balls.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar, and egg. Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder, soda, and salt. Chill dough.
Roll into balls size of large walnuts.
Place 3 inch apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour, criss-cross.
Bake until set but not hard, at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: golden graham s'mores
directions: Grease rectangular pan, 9 x 13 x 2-inch.
Heat syrup, margarine and morsels to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in large bowl.
Toss until coated.
Fold in marshmallows 1 cup at a time.
Press in pan.
Let stand to cool.
Cut into squares.
Store loosely covered up to 2 days.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Cover potatoes and onions with water to 1/2 inch above potatoes. Cook approximately 45 minutes. Add salts, Butter Buds, sherry and pepper. Stir well. Add cheese, stirring until melted.

title: chocolate oatmeal squares
directions: Melt margarine, stir in brown sugar, vanilla, and oatmeal. Cook over medium heat 2 - 3 minutes.
Press 1/2 mixture in a 9 inch square pan.
Melt choc. chips and add peanut butter.
Spread over oatmeal crust.
Sprinkle rest of oatmeal mixture over top of chocolate.

title: apricot brazil nut melts
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; cream until fluffy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add nuts and mix well.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Flatten with bottom of glass that has been dipped into flour.
Make indentation in center of cookie.
Bake in hot oven (375°) for about 4 minutes.
Remove from oven; press center again.
Fill with a little apricot jam and return to oven for another 4 to 6 minutes, until edges are light golden.
Cool on rack.
Decorate each cookie with 3 slices of Brazil nuts, arranged spoke fashion.
In center, place pieces of red and green cherries. Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: meat loaf
