directions: Mix together beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Put into pan.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over loaf.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Baste occasionally.

title: cheese nibblers
directions: Mix ingredients with pastry blender.
Knead in bowl until thoroughly combined.
Shape into balls, 1 teaspoon of dough each. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: blueberry sauce(for cheesecake, waffles, tarts and ice cream)
directions: Rinse berries.
Mix together dry ingredients in a saucepan; add liquids and stir until smooth.
Add blueberries, bring to a boil and cook for about 2 minutes or until clear and slightly thickened, stirring carefully to avoid crushing the berries. Serve warm or cold.

title: overnight breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Place bread in bottom of dish, then cheese, then sausage.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over bread mixture.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: parmesan oven chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Dip chicken breast in salad dressing.
Dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken in shallow baking pan coated with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: clam dip for vegetables
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and sour cream.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 cup of liquid from the clams, add soup mix.
Mix together until smooth, then add Worcestershire sauce and clams.
Pepper to taste.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Put sugar over the nuts and fruits.
Set aside.

title: lazy mary stuffed cabbage
directions: Brown meat; set aside.
Chop cabbage leaves into less then 1 1/2-inch squares.
Place into a greased roasting pan.
Layer the cabbage.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on cabbage.
Place meat on top of layered cabbage.
Pour tomato sauce over layer.
Pour tomato soup and 10 1/2 ounces of water onto layers.
Dice onion and layer.
Pour rice over surface.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir often while baking.
Easily serves eight.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into small pieces.
Cook in boiling salted water until tender; drain and set aside.
Saute sausage, onions, celery and pepper until done.
Add eggplant to sausage. Soak cracker crumbs in milk to soften.
Add crumbs and eggs to mixture.
Bake in a shallow pan for about 25 minutes or until brown at 350°.
If hot sausage is used, omit black pepper.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Butter the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and line bottom with bread after crusts are removed.
Brown sausage; scramble and drain.
Spread sausage over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage and bread.
Mix milk, eggs, mustard and cream of mushroom soup; beat until well blended.
Pour over cheese.
Cover and chill overnight.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, nuts and chips.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a baking dish with a cover.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over chicken breasts.
Bake in covered dish at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Baste every 20 minutes.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Remove 1 cup starter (refrigerate remainder, covered, feeding every 3 to 5 days).
Mix all ingredients in large bowl that has been greased.
Turn dough over once so it is greased on all sides. Cover lightly with foil.
Allow to stand at room temperature overnight or 8 to 12 hours.
After 8 to 12 hours, punch down and turn out on floured surface.
Knead a little.
Divide into 3 parts. Knead at least 12 to 15 times.
Shape into loaf.
Place into greased loaf pan.

Brush tops lightly with oil or melted butter. Cover and let rise out of draft (about 4 to 5 hours or all night). Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until dark golden brown and sounds hollow when tapped.
Brush tops with margarine.
Takes 3 pans, 9 x 5-inch.

title: late sandwich supper
directions: Mix butter, onion, garlic salt, parsley and poppy seed together. Spread on buns. Divide and add ham and cheese to buns. Wrap in foil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in 4 pieces.
Mix 1 tablespoon cinnamon and sugar in a bowl.
Coat each piece with this mixture and place in a greased Bundt pan.
Melt margarine, brown sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon in a saucepan.
Cook until it starts to boil; pour over biscuits and place in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from pan and enjoy.

title: freda's crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except cornflakes and melted butter).
Place in 3-quart 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Now, cover with 2 cups buttered cornflakes (4 to 5 tablespoons butter to 4 to 5 cups of cornflakes will make 2 cups crushed buttered cornflakes). Bake at 350° (uncovered) for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat; add chopped onion if desired.
Add Ragu sauce, brown sugar, tomato sauce and a few squirts ketchup.
Let simmer.
Cook noodles in water with a teaspoon of oil and a little salt.
Boil until done, about 10 minutes.
Mix cottage cheese and Mozzarella together.
Layer in pan lasagna, meat, cheese, lasagna, meat and cheese.
Cook in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
(Do not add salt.)
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: special occasion mashed potatoes
directions: Mash hot peppers.
Add cream cheese and butter in pieces.
Beat until both melted.
Mix in sour cream.
To milk, add eggs and onions; whip lightly.
Add to potato mixture along with seasonings. Beat until light and fluffy.
Place in greased 9-inch round casserole dish.
Refrigerate several hours (can be chilled overnight if not needed immediately).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8 to 12.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Store in refrigerator in covered bowl.
Use desired portions.
This batter will keep for several days.
Spoon
batter into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut off wing tips from wings and discard.
Cut remaining wings at the joint.
Put wings in crock-pot and add chicken bouillon. Cook on low 3 to 4 hours.
Drain.
Put on broiler tray.
Combine salt, pepper, cornstarch, brown sugar and ginger.
Brush sauce on wings.
Broil until glazed.
Turn and repeat on other side.

title: cheese onion spread
directions: Blend together all ingredients and use as needed.

title: fresh fruit dessert
directions: Gently mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Spoon into individual serving dishes and chill for at least 1 hour.
Just before serving, sprinkle brown sugar over each serving. For extra color, top with a maraschino cherry.

title: frying pan fudge
directions: Chop nuts and set aside.
Mix sugar, margarine and milk together in a heavy frying pan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook 6 more minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
stir until fudge begins to form.
Then quickly add vanilla.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Combine oats, flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly. Pat half of mixture in bottom of greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour pie filling over oat mixture.
Spoon remaining oat mixture over pie filling.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: crisp pickle slices(bread and butter)
directions: Slice cucumbers thin; add onions, pepper and garlic cold.
Add salt. Cover with cracked ice.
Mix.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Heat just to boiling.
Seal in hot sterilized jars. Makes 8 pints.

title: daisy's meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except can of soup, 1/4 can of water and optional mushrooms together.
Shape into small meatballs.
Brown in skillet.
Then add soup, 1/4 can of soup and optional mushrooms.
Simmer about 45 minutes, stirring often to prevent sticking.

title: sausage pilaf
directions: Brown sausage, drain off excess fat.
Add celery, onion and pepper.
Stir in pimento, soup, milk, rice and seasonings.
Pour in ungreased casserole.
Bake, covered, for 50 minutes at 350°, stirring occasionally.
Mix crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes longer.
Trim with pimento cutouts.

title: fourteen day pickles
directions: Use a churn or some type of crock pot (No Plastic). Heat water to boiling and add salt. Dissolve and pour over cucumbers. Weigh cucumbers down in salt water so they are covered. Let stand seven days. Drain off water. Heat

1 gal. water to boiling and pour over drained cucumbers. Let stand for 24 hours and drain that water off. Add fresh boiling water with alum the size of a walnut and let stand twenty four hours. Drain off this mixture.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat
eggs until creamy.
Stir in corn.
Add dry ingredients. Mix
well
until
smooth.
Pour
in
Pam coated dish. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes, until brown on top.

title: fudge batter pudding
directions: Mix flour, 3 Tbsp. cocoa and 1/2 tsp. salt (set aside).

title: betty's hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat in skillet over medium heat.
Drain fat and set aside.
Blend next 4 ingredients until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Turn into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown on top and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer salad in order given.
Cover and chill overnight.
Toss well just before serving.

title: quick and easy soda biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and bake for 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 12.

title: garlic-lemon green beans
directions: Saute in oil or butter the mushrooms and garlic.
Cook green beans to your liking of crispness.

title: icebox fruit roll
directions: Knead into a roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and place in refrigerator for several hours.
Slice and serve with whipped cream.

title: fast sweet potatoes
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl.
Use mixer to whip ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake about 40 minutes.

title: orange french toast
directions: Place butter on a sided cookie sheet and melt in a 400° oven. Mix sugar, cinnamon (and orange rind, optional) and sprinkle evenly in the pan.
Mix eggs and juice and dip bread.
Arrange in pan.
Spoon on remaining mixture.
Serve sugar side up.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Freezes nicely.

title: santa fe chicken
directions: Debone and cube chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet, over medium-high heat.
Cook chicken in oil 2 minutes.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; cook until tender (4 minutes), stirring frequently.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar, salt and Karo.
Mix well and boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and stir.
Then add soda and stir quickly.
Pour over corn.
Place in a roaster pan.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: 6-cup salad
directions: Drain all fruits, then add sour cream and stir.

title: "mama's" cornbread
directions: This is best baked in a cast-iron frying pan.

title: banana walnut cake
directions: Cream the butter, add the sugar gradually, creaming well. Add the eggs and beat well.
Sift the flour with the salt, soda and baking powder in a separate bowl.
Add the walnuts.
Combine the banana and sour milk alternately with the dry ingredients to the sugar mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: florida lime pie
directions: In top part of double boiler, mix egg yolks, sugar and lime juice.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until thickened.
Add grated rind.
Chill until thickened, but not firm.
Whip 1 cup cream and fold in.
Add a few drops coloring.
Pile in shell and chill about 24 hours.

title: best peanut butter pie
directions: In large bowl, combine cream cheese and peanut butter at medium speed until well blended.
Add powdered sugar and 1 egg; beat until smooth and creamy.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into baked pie shell.
Garnish with more whipped topping, if desired.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Make plain or add favorite fruit.

title: summer squash or zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in boiling salted water for 5 minutes. Drain; combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots.
Fold in squash and onions.
Combine stuffing and butter.
Spread half of stuffing on bottom of 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: easy no bake peanut butter cheesecake
directions: Prepare Chocolate Crumb Crust; set aside.

title: chocolate butterscotch squares
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients, nuts and chocolate.
Mix well.
Spread in a greased jelly roll pan, 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar and cut into squares while warm.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: nancy's cream cheese pound cake
directions: Variation that is great:
Leave
off the vanilla and add 1 tablespoon butternut flavoring and add 1 cup chopped walnuts.

title: italian soup
directions: Remove casing from sausage and brown in kettle.
Drain off fat, breaking with spoon.
Add celery and onion and cook 10 minutes. Add other ingredients except zucchini and peppers.
Simmer covered 20 minutes.
Now add peppers and zucchini and cook covered 10 minutes.
Do not add water.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together the flour, soda and salt. Add both sugars, egg, vanilla and shortening.
Mix together until smooth and well blended. Add the nuts (if desired) and chocolate chips. Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: yum-yummier sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in small saucepan and mix well.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens, stirring frequently.
Spread on top of cooked meat loaf and bake for additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: delicious meat
directions: Mix ingredients together in a Tupperware marinating dish.
Put instant tenderizer meat tenderizer on all areas of the roast and use a fork to pierce the roast and allow the tenderizer to get into the roast.
Place roast in marinade and seal with the top of the dish.
Marinate for 24 hours, turning dish a few times during that time to make sure all areas of the roast are marinated.
Broil or barbecue 20 minutes per side.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Slowly add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Continue mixing until thick and foamy.
Stir in zucchini.
In another bowl, stir together the flour, nutmeg, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir dry ingredients gently into zucchini mixture until just blended.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing to rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind together zucchini, peppers, onions and celery. Add salt and let stand overnight in refrigerator. Next day, drain; rinse with a little cold water (sort of press the water out of it). Then add remaining ingredients; mix and cook for 15 minutes. Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased glass baking dish.
Combine dry ingredients and work in melted butter.
Sprinkle over apples and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in cooked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.

title: italian beef
directions: Cut roast in half. Place in a 5-quart slow cooker. Combine the water and seasoning. Pour over roast. Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours or until the meat is very tender. Discard bay leaf. Remove meat and shred with a fork. Skim fat from cooking juices. Return meat to slow cooker. Yields 14 servings.

title: mushrooms florentine
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Place 2 tablespoons of the butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add the mushrooms and cook until browned, browning the cap sides first.
Stir the salt, onion and remaining butter into the spinach.
Line a 10-inch casserole with the spinach mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of the cheese over the spinach.
Arrange the browned mushrooms over the cheese.
Season with the garlic salt and top with the remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Bake for 20 minutes or until the cheese is melted and browned. Serve hot.

title: herbed green beans
directions: Cook beans in slightly salted water; cover pan and cook for 15 minutes or until tender.
Melt butter in small pan.
Add onion, garlic and basil.
Simmer about 4 minutes.
Add seasonings.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes longer.

title: blueberry coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, baking powder and soda.
Alternating, add flour and sour cream. Fold in blueberries.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8 x 8-inch pans.

title: curried swiss bites
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together well.
Cut biscuits in half and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Put 1 teaspoon of mix on each half-biscuit.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes until filling is set in center.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix salmon and egg with fork.
Add 1/2 cup sifted flour.
Add pepper, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
In 1/4 cup salmon juice, add baking powder and beat with fork until foams.
Pour into salmon mixture. Form into patties and fry in hot oil until browned and onion is tender.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown beef, onion and green peppers together.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over rice or pasta.
Makes enough for 6 to 8 people.

title: darlene's sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add flour last.
Measure out by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten by stamping with a flat-bottomed glass covered with a damp cloth and dipped in sugar.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on English muffins.
Cut in quarters.
Broil for 2 minutes or until bubbly.

title: agnes moorehead's whipped avocado
directions: Cut chilled avocados in half a few minutes before serving. Remove pulp, keeping the skin intact.
Whip pulp, sugar and lime juice to a smooth, velvety cream (about 5 minutes).
Pile back into skins and serve at once with lime wedges.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees, mix together all ingredients with electric mixer. Spray 2 - 9 inch rounds. Pour batter equally in pans. Bake 20 minutes. Cool on rack for 10 minutes.

title: carrot cake(20 servings)
directions: Mix in a large bowl and beat hard. Bake in large bundt pan, tube pan or large oblong pan. Depending on size of pan cake will take from 45 minutes to 1 1/2 hours. Bake at 350°.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil together squash and onions and drain.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Use about 3/4 pound Velveeta cheese cut into fairly thick slices.
Make a layer over squash.
Take Kraft soft margarine (must be Kraft) and put a thick layer over cheese.
Crush a roll of Town House crackers and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
This can also be used for broccoli.

title: sonora shrimp
directions: In large heavy skillet, melt margarine and saute bell pepper, onion and celery.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp; blend well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp and cook 10 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Serve over hot fluffy rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter apple dip
directions: In a mixing bowl combine ingredients. Mix well. Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix
chicken,
soup and milk together.	Place in baking dish and
top
with
stuffing (already prepared).
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and brown.

title: school day casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients except grated cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake in 375° oven until bubbly, about 25 minutes.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until hard ball stage, 250° on thermometer.
Slowly pour onto the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Keep beating until set and add the vanilla.
Spoon onto waxed paper to make individual pieces of candy.

title: gingerbread
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add molasses and beaten eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to molasses mix alternately with the milk. Add spices and nuts.
Bake in two shallow pans.
When cool, put together with applesauce.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice, lemon rind and yolks until smooth. Pour into crust.

title: cornbread and pinto bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; toss and serve.

title: biscuit coffee ring
directions: Grease 9-inch round cake pan.
Blend sugar and cinnamon together.
Melt margarine.
Separate biscuits and dip in melted margarine; coat entirely with sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place 15 biscuits around outer circle of pan overlapping to fill circle, then overlap remaining 5 biscuits around inner circle.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Top with chopped nuts. Bake in moderate oven preheated 425° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Spread cream cheese into bottom of microwave-safe dish.
Drain beans, and spread them on top of cream cheese.
Grate cheese over beans.
Microwave for ten minutes.
Serve with favorite chips.

title: story farm salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in a quart jar.
Let the onion and garlic soak in jar; do not chop.
Refrigerate.
Dressing is best if made 24 hours before use; flavor improves with age.

title: sugarless health cookies
directions: Cream
oleo
until soft.
Chop dates, nuts and raisins, in hot water
to
soften.
Sift soda and flour and add fruits and nuts. Beat
egg
and
add sugar substitute.
Combine oleo and egg mixture; add to flour mixture, stirring just enough to mix.
Drop by
teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until brown
and
a
toothpick stuck in center comes out clean, about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Fold fruit, nuts and marshmallows in half of Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Put remaining topping over pie decorated with maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: never fail rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add sugar, egg, salt and water.
Ad 1/2 of flour and beat well.
Add melted shortening and mix in remaining flour.
Let rise to double in size.
Punch down and knead.
Roll out and place in greased pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 425° until browned.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Line pizza pan with cookie dough slices overlapping.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla extract.
Spread over cookie crust.
Arrange fruit in circular pattern over cream cheese, starting with bananas on outside rim. Mix preserves and water and spread over fruit.
Be sure to cover all fruit so no discoloration occurs.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: lazy mans salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: frozen fruit cup
directions: Mix and freeze.
This dessert may be prepared several days ahead of time.

title: ritz cracker pecan pie
directions: Grease 9 inch pie plate to rim.
Beat egg whites till stiff. Crush Ritz crackers fine.
Chop pecans fine.
Add vanilla, sugar, crackers, and pecans to beaten egg whites.
Fold all together till blended.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 45 minutes; cool.
Cover cool pie and refrigerate overnight. When ready to serve, top with Cool-Whip.
This recipe will also make approximately 30 mini tarts.
Bake tarts for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain. Arrange broccoli in greased 2 quart casserole or baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of cheese.
Place chicken on cheese and broccoli.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and pour over chicken.
Top with other 1/2 cup cheese. Put bread crumbs on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Make salad. Add dressing and Fritos just before serving.

title: crunch-top potatoes
directions: Pour butter into baking pan.
Add potatoes in a single layer, turn once in butter.
Combine cheese, cornflakes and paprika and sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: brenda's zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugars, oil, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add raisins and black walnuts.
Beat well all the ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan.
Ingredients will fill 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° approximately 1 hour.

title: holiday wreath
directions: Combine marshmallows, butter, vanilla and food coloring in top of double boiler; heat until smooth, stirring frequently.
Take off stove; gradually add cereal.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper; cut in the shape of a 9-inch circle.
Add candied red cherries in groups of three.

title: sweet sour meat balls
directions: Mix well and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar, half the chopped peanuts and margarine until crumbly.
Stir in the beaten eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Mix well.
Press into bottom of 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in condensed milk, 2 remaining eggs, sugar and peanut butter. Add remaining teaspoon of vanilla and mix until smooth.
Pour over prepared crust and sprinkle the remaining peanuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until set.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and cranberry sauce.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 4 cup mold or individual molds. Chill until firm.
Unmold and serve.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients, except onion, in a food processor or blender and beat until very smooth.
Then add onions and again beat until smooth.
It can be served immediately or refrigerated (best this way).
Pour over fresh spinach and top with sauteed almond slices, bacon bits and thin sliced purple onion.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook the broccoli and onion until tender; drain.
Stir in butter, flour, chicken bouillon and milk.
Bring to a boil for a minute; then turn heat to low and add Cheez Whiz.

title: snowball cake
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over boiling water.
Stir until gelatin dissolves.
Add sugar, pineapple and lemon juice.
Stir well and refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Prepare 2 envelopes of Dream Whip.
Stir into gelatin mixture.

title: chicken and water chestnut casserole
directions: Mix first 5 together.
Put in 2-quart casserole and cover with topping (cornbread and butter).
Bake at 350° 30 to 40 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except raisins. Bake at 350° on a lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Mix occasionally while cooking to avoid burning. Judge time accordingly.
Mixture will darken when it comes out of oven.
Add raisins when cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: yellow squash and green bean saute
directions: In a large frying pan, bring 1/4 inch of lightly salted water to a boil.
Add beans and cook until tender, about 8 minutes. Drain beans and set aside.
Wipe out pan with a paper towel.
In the same pan, heat oil and butter over medium-high heat.
Add squash and cook 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in beans, dill, salt and pepper.
Cook until veggies are tender and crisp, stirring constantly, about 2 minutes.
Place in a serving bowl and serve immediately.

title: special k cookies
directions: Boil sugar and syrup for 1 minute, then add vanilla and 1 cup peanut butter.
Mix well.
Pour over cereal.
Mix and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: cheese ball
directions: Leave cream cheese at room temperature 5 or 6 hours.
Use food processor.
Blend beef. Put cheese, onions and both salts in and blend well. Chill for 4 or 5 hours. Roll into 2 balls. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: potato casserole supreme
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain and beat until fluffy.
Add butter, seasoning, milk, onions and bacon.
Fold cheese into whipped cream and spread over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Casserole may be prepared ahead of time and topping added just before baking.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine cream of mushroom soup, dry onion soup mix, milk and rice.
Put in oblong pan.
Add chicken and bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain salmon, bone and skin.
Mix thoroughly the next 5 ingredients.
Chill for several hours.
Shape into a log; garnish with parsley.
Serve with party crackers.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add corned beef, cheese, soup, milk and onion.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cut apples in very small pieces and mix with sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add butter and egg. Stir all together.

title: cream cheese party cupcakes
directions: Beat cream cheese in a large mixing bowl until soft and creamy.
Gradually add one cup sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in
1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Spoon batter into paper-lined miniature muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Combine sour cream, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, stirring well.
Spoon 1/4 teaspoon of sour cream mixture on each cupcake.
Top with small amount of strawberry preserves in the center of the sour cream mixture.
Return cupcakes to oven and continue baking for five minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cupcakes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and allow to cool.
Add bananas, marshmallows and pineapple.
Let it firm.

title: baked seafood casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together as making a seafood salad.
Fill baking pan and cover with crushed chips.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fish stew
directions: In a large nonstick pot, heat the oil over medium heat.
Add the garlic and onion.
Saute gently for 2 minutes.
Add the wine and cook for 2 minutes longer.

title: spiced acorn squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Split each squash in half lengthwise; scoop out and discard seeds and fiber from centers.
Slice a piece from the underside of each half so it rests flat.
Place, cut sides up, in a shallow baking dish.
Mix spices together and sprinkle over squash.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Combine melted butter and vinegar; drizzle over squash.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine sugar, dry mustard, salt, onion powder and	vinegar.
While
mixing
mixture, very, very slowly pour in the oil.
Add poppy seed and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Use over fresh fruit or green salad.
Makes 1 quart.

title: excellent mexican dip
directions: Heat refried beans in saucepan until soft and warm.
Flatten onto dinner plate.
Top with taco mix, then scallions, then tomato, then salsa, then sour cream, then Cheddar cheese, then olives.
You will now have an 8 layer dip.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Takes about 15 minutes to make.
No baking required.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth. Drain.
Add chicken, soups, Ro-Tel, onion, salt and pepper.
Top with cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: carol smith's one pan pork chop dinner
directions: In
an
electric
skillet, brown pork chops in a little oil. Add
the can of chicken gumbo soup and 1/2 can of water. Peel
and chunk
potatoes.
Add
potatoes,
peas, carrots and seasonings to
skillet.
Mix together.
Cover and cook for 40 minutes at 375°.
(Check
to
see if you need to add a little more water after about 20 minutes.) Serve with rolls.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, soup and ham.
Fold in drained vegetables. Bake covered 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly butter a 12-inch pizza pan.
Slice cookies in 1/8 or 1/4-inch slices and cover the pizza pan, slightly overlapping the edges.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Beat sugar, vanilla and cream cheese until creamy. Spread over baked cookie dough.
Arrange fruit in pattern over pizza.
Dilute preserves with water and coat top.
Be sure all fruit is covered to keep from turning brown.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Servings:

title: fresh tomato cheese rarebit
directions: Chop tomatoes and onion and set aside.
Heat soup with milk and mustard mixed in.
Toast bread.
Pile tomatoes and onion on toast and pour soup mixture over this.

title: low-fat oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the oil, sugars, egg whites, molasses and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture. Add chocolate bits or raisins.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: beef skillet rice fiesta
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add V-8 juice, chili powder, pepper flakes, corn and tomatoes.
Let come to a boil. Add Minute rice.
Cover and let sit 7 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; let jell.
Mix rest of ingredients into jello.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix cottage cheese, eggs, Parmesan cheese and parsley together and let set at least 1/2 hour, longer if possible.
Brown meat and drain, then add sauce and 1/2 jar of water; simmer.
Spray pan with Pam and put 1 cup sauce in bottom of pan, then layer of uncooked noodles, then layer meat sauce and then layer of cheese mixture. Repeat layers until pan is full.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°; uncover and top with Mozzarella and cook 15 minutes more.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Mix together the brown sugar, catsup, mustard, salt, pepper, white sugar, barbecue sauce and chili powder.
Mix with the cooked beef, bacon and onion.
Add the beans.
Mix all together.
Pour into crock-pot; cook on low for 1 hour or more.
Serve with cornbread.

title: peanut butter favorites
directions: Combine the peanut butter
and	butter in a large bowl. Add the other ingredients and
mix
well.
Roll the dough into 1-inch balls and arrange 3
inches
apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press crisscross
pattern on the cookies with a fork. Bake at 350° until	golden	brown,	about 10 to 12 minutes.
Allow to cool before taking them up.

title: strawberry cream jello salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello in boiling water.
Add 1 cup strawberry juice from thawed frozen strawberries.
Put in refrigerator until set.
Mix in sour cream, Philadelphia cream cheese and drained strawberries.
Pour into bowl.
Set and serve later.

title: corn salad
directions: Add all ingredients and lightly mix.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: apple-cheese refrigerator cake
directions: Cut pound cake crosswise in thin slices.
Combine Ricotta and sugar; mix well.
Stir in chocolate, apple and almond extract. Spread generously between cake slices, putting together in loaf shape.
Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in Jell-O mold. Refrigerate until thoroughly set.
Unmold and serve.

title: braised pork chops
directions: Brown on both sides in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Remove chops from skillet; layer remaining ingredients into skillet.
Add chops.
Add water and cover skillet tightly.
Cook over low heat 15 to 20 minutes or until pork and cabbage are tender.
Add water if it seems dry.
Yields 2 servings.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring cocoa, water and oleo to a boil.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl.
Add cocoa mixture and mix well by hand.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes on greased cookie sheet with sides.

title: rooibeet slaai(red beet salad from south africa)
directions: Combine beets and onion in bowl.
Mix sugar, salt and vinegar together.
Pour over beets and mix well.
Marinate for 30 minutes. Serve cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs, mashed bananas and other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: good for you pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients and mix briefly.
Blueberries can be added, if desired.

title: mini pies
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese together and add remaining ingredients.
Roll out on floured surface and using biscuit cutter, cut into circles.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of preserves or fruit spread in center.
Fold over and press edges together with a fork.
Be sure to use a toothpick or fork and insert holes on top of pies. These mini pies will resemble the shape of a fried pie only baked instead of fried.
These make great finger foods for showers or teas and may be garnished with a dusting of powdered sugar.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the egg and
beat
well.
Add salad oil and beat again.
Add corn flakes, oatmeal,
coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add
this to the mixture along with the vanilla.
Shape dough
into
balls
the
size of hickory nuts. Place them on an ungreased cookie sheet and press flat with a fork that has been dipped in melted butter and sugar.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles for 3 minutes in boiling salted water; drain. Brown ground beef, garlic and onion in salad oil.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Fill 1 1/2-quart casserole by alternating layers of noodles, Mozzarella cheese, tomato-meat mixture and Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients, then add the others and mix until lumps are gone, using a slotted spoon.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Ice with your favorite frosting.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken; cover with crushed crackers, mixed with butter.
Sprinkle top with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: busy day meal
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; form into balls the size of a walnut.
Pour soup and string beans and juice over.
Cook until hamburger is done.
Remove from pan to a casserole dish.
Put biscuits on top and bake in oven until biscuits are done.
This is real good.
Can be poured over rice or eaten with mashed potatoes.

title: beach balls
directions: Drain clams; reserve liquid.
Add water to clam liquid to make 1 cup.
In saucepan, combine liquid butter, poultry seasoning and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Add flour and cook until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Stir in clams.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
